title: skinny soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a big pot and simmer over low heat until vegetables are tender, 1 hour or more. Add more broth if needed.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with Cool Whip. Fold in pie filling and pineapple. Pour into serving dish and chill for several hours.

title: punch
directions: Soften the sherbet.
Add the thawed orange juice and cold ginger ale.
I always use some Seven-Up.
Also, I use orange juice to taste.
Stir well and serve right away.
Punch should be slightly thick.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Cut up the cauliflower and broccoli and add onions.
Mix salad dressing with mayonnaise and add to the vegetable mixture.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain.
In saucepan, add oleo, sugar and water.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves, stirring often.
Add carrots and simmer until hot.

title: christmas salad
directions: For each plate, 1 ring of pineapple, 1/2 banana and 1 maraschino cherry.
Place pineapple slice on shredded lettuce, then place 1/2 of a straight banana in a pineapple ring.
Split the top of the banana four ways not too far down.
Fill the split with salad dressing and let it run down on banana like tallow from a candle, then place cherry on top for the flame.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix all except cranberry sauce; divide into parts.
Press one part in 2-quart baking dish.
Slice cranberry sauce fairly thin and put layer on top.
Top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: nut cake
directions: Melt butter; beat in eggs to which cocoa has been added.
Add sugar and mix well.
Sift flour with dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: chewy ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses.
Then sift remaining dry ingredients and add.
Roll into walnut-size balls. Roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: creamy veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in 2-quart casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tropical shake
directions: Toss banana with lemon juice; drain, reserving lemon juice. Place banana slices on a baking sheet, and freeze 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Process banana slices, reserved lemon juice, mango, 1 1/2 cups pineapple-orange juice, and yogurt in a blender until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides.
Pour into chilled glasses; serve immediately.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Combine the oil, lemon juice, garlic powder and hot sauce in a skillet that has been coated with butter-flavored no-stick cooking spray.
Saut the shrimp in the oil mixture until they turn pink. Serve with steamed rice.
Makes 4 servings, 6 fat grams per serving.

title: sakis
directions: Mix ingredients (except chicken) in food processor.
Marinate chicken for 6 hours (or up to 3 days).
Skewer and cook over low grill until done.
Takes about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crispy oven-fried chicken(makes 4 servings)
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Line a baking sheet with foil.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers, cut up candied cherries and pineapple. Leave nuts whole.
Mix all ingredients, one at a time, except milk and marshmallows.
Melt milk and marshmallows and stir into fruit mixture.
Pack into an angel food cake pan.
Store in closed container in a cool place.

title: leftover pinto bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Stir well. Pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bacon is done. Serve hot.

title: mexi-corn casserole
directions: Fix rice as directed on package.
Combine rice, corn, butter and soup.
Mix all together and pour into casserole dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple and coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add all other ingredients; pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in slow oven at 300° about 45 minutes or until set.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into muffin pans that have been greased or lined with baking cups. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen miniature muffins or 12 large muffins.

title: quiche
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Fry peppers and onions in grease.
Add cheese and other ingredients.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: tailgating mix
directions: Pour cereal into a large bowl.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Dribble over cereal.
With a spoon, toss and coat the mixture.
Add 10x sugar.
Place seal on bowl to shake (or place entire mixture into a large plastic bag to seal and shake).

title: onion pie
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pastry shell with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently prick again with a fork.
Bake 5 minutes more and let cool.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onions in 3 tablespoons bacon drippings until tender.
Combine bacon, onions and next 4 ingredients in bowl; stir well.
Spoon mixture into pastry shell and sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: fresh gooseberry pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 2-crust 9-inch pie.
Combine first 4 ingredients; cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.
Add whole berries.
Fill pastry shell.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust, cutting slits; seal.
Bake at 400°
for 30 to 40 minutes, or until crust is brown.
Serve warm.

title: mac and two cheese
directions: Boil and drain macaroni according to directions.
Grate cheeses.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter.
Layer macaroni alternately with cheeses 4 times or until all ingredients are used up.
Pour milk in until baking dish is 3/4 of the way full.
Add pats of butter to top layer and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; save 2 cans broth.
Debone chicken.
Mix together 2 cans of broth with soup.
Pour into bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken, pulled apart into bite size bits.
Mix together the flour, salt, pepper, buttermilk and margarine; pour over top of chicken in casserole.
(This will form its own crust and top.)
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: heath bars
directions: Line 4 sided cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Take oleo, butter, sugar and salt and boil for 3 minutes.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts to syrup.
Pour over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Remove to cooling rack covered with waxed paper to cool.

title: peach-cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Place peach gelatin in a bowl.
Bring 2 cups of water to a boil and pour over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice, mix well.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in peaches. Pour into 3 qt. serving bowl.
Chill until firm.
Place cranberry gelatin in another bowl, bring remaining water to a boil; pour over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cranberry juice and mix well.
In a blender combine combine oranges, cranberries and sugar, process until fruit is coarsely chopped.
Add to cranberry gelatin.
Carefully spoon over peach gelatin.
Chill until set.

title: effie's butterscotch pound cake
directions: First 3 ingredients should be at room temperature. Cream first 3. Add sugar and vanilla. Beat well. Add eggs, one at a time (these should be at room temperature), beating after each egg. Add flour to mixture slowly. Save a little flour to dust nuts and butterscotch pieces, then add to mixture. Cook in tube pan or 2 loaves at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole i
directions: Place cooked broccoli cuts in a greased, oblong baking dish. Melt margarine; add onion and saute until tender.
Add soups and cheese.
Melt together slowly.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: grandma francis 5 cup cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, until smooth and firm. Fold in a total of 5 cups of any of the ingredients
following.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Roll out pastry 1/2 inch thick, and cut into 6 squares.
Place an apple in the center of each square.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg and 2 tablespoons butter.
Fill the apples with the mixture.
Moisten edges of pastry with cold water and fold up around apples, sealing all cracks.
Prick with a fork.
Chill 1 hour.
Combine rest of ingredients and 2 cups of hot water; boil for 5 minutes.
Place apples in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake 10 minutes at 450°. Reduce to 350° and pour syrup over the apples.
Bake 35 minutes, basting often.
Serves 6.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in two 9-inch pans.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, jello and cornstarch together in a saucepan.
Add water; mix.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly and boil 5 minutes.
Pour into bowl and let cool.
Pour over whole stemmed strawberries.
Then pour into crust.
Chill; top with Cool Whip.

title: glaze for ham or pork
directions: Combine ingredients; heat.
Spoon over meat while cooking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: overnight egg casserole
directions: Grease casserole and alternate layers of bread, cheese, mushrooms and ham.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over bread mixture.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°.

title: corn relish
directions: In large Dutch oven or pan, combine corn, cabbage, onions and peppers.
In a bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars, 1/4-inch head space. Adjust caps.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Let stand at least 1 week to blend flavors.
Yields about 14 jars (12 ounces each).
Very good on hamburgers, hot dogs or eat alone.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine flour with sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Prepare Cream Cheese Topping.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Marinate brisket in liquid smoke overnight, covered.
Drain next day and sprinkle paprika, garlic and pepper on brisket.
Slice onion and celery and cover seasoned brisket.
Wrap tightly in foil and bake in slow oven at 250° for 5 or 6 hours, according to size of brisket.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Drain and remove celery and onion.
Slice and pour barbecue sauce over sliced brisket and return to a 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: steak dish
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and brown on both sides in the butter.
Remove to a casserole.
To the fat in the pan, add the onion and cook until brown.
Stir in the flour and seasonings and slowly add the water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 300°. Bake for 2 hours.
Be sure the meat is completely covered with gravy when in oven.

title: minestrone soup(weight watchers)
directions: Place all ingredients in large soup pot.
Cover with water. Cook until all vegetables are tender.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine oats, corn syrup, eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt, mixing well.
Add melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pastry shell and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with a layer of uncrumbled graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk and Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over bottom layer of crackers.
Repeat a layer of crackers; pour remaining pudding over crackers.
Top pudding with third layer of crackers.
Spread chocolate butter icing over top layer of crackers.
Chill at least 24 hours (for crackers to soften) before serving.

title: peach preserves
directions: Put 1 pint of peaches and 1 pint sugar in large heavy pan. Cook slowly until sugar dissolves.
Turn heat up and bring to rolling boil for 10 minutes.
Add another pint of peaches and pint of sugar.
Again bring to rolling boil and boil for 10 more minutes.
Seal in clean hot jars.

title: sour cream pound cake #6
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar;
add
eggs
one at a time and beat well after each egg. Add
flavoring
and
beat.	Measure 3 cups flour and add soda
to flour.
Add
flour	and sour cream to butter mixture alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours
to	1
1/2 hours at 325°.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes before
removing. This
cake	will
stay
moist 2 weeks if it lasts that long.

title: stuffed cymling or patty pan squash(white squash)
directions: Steam squash (whole).
When almost tender, drain and cool. Scoop out centers, leaving a shell about 1/2-inch thick.
Chop the removed pulp.
Add to removed pulp other ingredients.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Refill the shells.
Place them in a pan, in very little water or on a rack above the water.
Bake until hot, about 10 minutes.
(Makes a pretty dish.)
Yields 4 servings.

title: butternut squash and parsnip soup
directions: In a large stockpot over medium heat, warm the oil; then add the squash, carrots, parsnips and onion.
Cook the vegetables, stirring occasionally, until they are slightly tender and warmed through, about 5 minutes.
Add the thyme, coriander, chicken stock, salt, pepper, vinegar and bay leaf.
Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook until the vegetables are soft, about 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and thyme sprigs and puree the mixture in batches in a blender until smooth, 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients with zucchini and nuts.
Beat eggs and add oil to eggs.
Mix with the dry ingredients until moist.
Place in greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon-angel dessert
directions: Make lemon pudding following the directions on the box, except fold hot lemon pudding into the beaten meringue.
Pour half this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear angel food cake into chunks and sink into lemon/meringue mixture in pan.
Pour remaining lemon/meringue over top.
Chill until set.
Serve as made or top with fresh strawberries, blueberries or cherry pie filling.
Makes 15 servings (plain) with 205 calories and 1 gram fat each.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Cook angel hair pasta, enough for 4, in a large pot.
While that is cooking, saute shrimp in olive oil, butter and garlic until pink.
Drain pasta; add to shrimp.
Toss, adding cheese and dill.
Ready to serve.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Beat avocados, onion, peppers, lemon juice, salt, pepper and ascorbic acid mixture until creamy.
Fold in tomato.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stir before serving. Makes 2 cups dip.

title: fried white potatoes
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp. Remove bacon from skillet, reserving drippings. Drain bacon on paper towel, then crumble and set aside. Cook potatoes in bacon drippings for 10 minutes or until browned, turning frequently. Drain. Place potatoes in serving dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and crumbled bacon.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil and drain lasagne noodles.
Follow package directions. While noodles are boiling, brown meat in skillet. Empty pasta sauce in saucepan and add meat and sugar.
In baking dish (about 13 x 9-inch), alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese mix, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Use sauce for top layer. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 375° oven. Serves 6.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Place in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until firm.
Drain well. Cook bacon, remove from pan and crumble on paper towel.
Saute onion in bacon grease. Add onion, butter, cheese, sour cream, crackers, salt and pepper to squash. Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 40 minutes. Last five minutes sprinkle
with cheese and crackers. Brown and serve.

title: baked vegetable dish
directions: Shred cabbage; peel and shred carrots.
Put all vegetables in a bowl and mix in salt, sugar, lemon juice and melted butter. Stir well.
Pack mixture into a 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Combine cabbage, water and salt in saucepan.
Place lid on pan and cook ten minutes.
Make sauce of milk, cheese and cornstarch; cook until thick.

title: best ever spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Remove excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes or longer.
Freezes well.
Ummm good!!

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and cook according to directions on package.
Cool 15 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients.
Doritos must be crushed up.
Add Catalina dressing just before serving.

title: kitzy's sausage and cabbage
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Stirring often.
Add sliced potatoes and onion.
Fry until slightly brown.
Add thinly sliced cabbage, salt and pepper.
Cover and steam just until cabbage is tender.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: Cook meat in just enough water to cover until fat appears on water.
Drain meat thoroughly.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to boil and cook over low heat until as thick as desired.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: hot and sour scallop soup
directions: Bring chicken broth, mushrooms and bamboo shoots to boil. Reduce heat, simmer 5 minutes.
Add scallops, soy sauce and pepper and bring to boil.
Slowly add cornstarch mixture and stir a few seconds until thickened.
Stir soup briskly with chopstick or long handle of spoon; gradually pour in egg.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar.
Ladle into bowls and serve garnished with green onion.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour water and milk in a sauce pan.
Bring to simmer.
Add cornmeal and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together and place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: country style fried rice
directions: Brown hamburger and dump into large pot. While hamburger is browning, make Minute rice according to directions and dump into hamburger. Stir-fry celery, carrots and poppy seeds. Add to hamburger and rice mix.
Heat well and serve. Makes a quick and easy meal in one.

title: fried quail
directions: Salt, pepper and roll quail in flour.
Fry in deep fat until brown (save drippings for cream gravy).
Wrap quail tightly in foil and cook in oven for 2 hours at 250°.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve with hot biscuits, gravy and rice.

title: green rice
directions: Saute in margarine green pepper, onion and celery (chopped). Mix rice, Cheez Whiz, soup and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Add chili powder beginning with 2 tablespoons. Simmer and serve.

title: hot fudge for sundaes
directions: In a heavy medium size saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stirring constantly,
cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over ice cream.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in flour and brown in oil.

title: crustless ham quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° until firm and browned, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken philippine style
directions: Marinate chicken in mixture of other ingredients for 30 minutes.
This can be done
in skillet to be used for cooking. Heat on top of stove until
it
comes
to
a
boil.
Cover and simmer about 40 minutes or
until almost all liquid has evaporated.
Serve hot or cold.

title: melt-in-your-mouth turkey pie
directions: Break turkey into bite-size pieces.
Place in casserole dish; cover with sliced eggs.
Bring soup and broth to boil and pour over chicken.
Melt margarine.
Mix in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, for smooth consistency.
Pour over turkey evenly.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna linguine toss
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, cook linguine according to package directions, adding carrots during last 5 minutes of cooking.
Drain.
In jar or cruet, combine bottled lemon juice, water, oil, dill and garlic salt.
Shake well.
In large bowl, combine linguine, carrots, broccoli, mushrooms, onions, tuna and Parmesan cheese.
Add 1 cup dressing; mix well.
Cover.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, toss with remaining dressing.
Serve with additional Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinated chicken italiano
directions: In shallow dish, pour dressing over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, 3 hours or overnight.
Remove chicken; reserve marinade.
Grill or broil, turning and basting frequently with reserved marinade, until done. Do not brush with marinade during last 5 minutes of cooking. Makes about 4 servings.

title: light and lively salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: dad's 14-day pickles
directions: 1st Day:
Wash and pack a gallon whole cukes in a jar.
Make a brine of 1 cup salt and boiling water (to cover cukes).

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup.
Add salt and gelatin, which has been dissolved in water.
Add cream cheese which has been beaten beforehand.
Cool.

title: easy chicken
directions: Pour rice evenly in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice.
Stir soup and broth together and pour 1/2 of the soup mixture over the rice.
Place chicken breasts on the rice.
Pour the other 1/2 of the soup mixture over the chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: mary's chocolate pie
directions: Mix
1	cup sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, milk and water in pan. Cook
until
thick.
Pour
into cooled cooked pie shell. Beat
egg yolks
until
stiff.
Add	2
teaspoons sugar; beat again.
Bake in 400° oven until top is brown.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: In top of double boiler, stir water, jello, marshmallows and cream cheese until melted.
Cool slightly, about 15 minutes.
Add cranberries, pecans and pineapple.
Chill and serve.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Peel and chop onion. Beat egg well, add corn, onion, and salt and pepper to taste to bread crumbs and milk. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: porky sparerib delight
directions: Place salt and peppered spareribs in a shallow roasting pan. Brown 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to drained ribs; return to oven 40 to 50 minutes longer. You may use pork meat chunks instead of ribs.
Brown the meat; drain.
Pour the sauce over and bake 1 hour.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Brush chicken pieces with milk.
Pat crushed stuffing mix onto each piece.
Shake off excess crumbs.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, in a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until chicken tests done.

title: tomato jello salad
directions: In hot water dissolve Jell-O; mix well, then add tomatoes, again mix well.
Let set.

title: dirt
directions: Scrape cream filling off 24 cookies.
Mix pudding, milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip in mixer.
Fold in crushed Oreos.
Spoon into a clean flowerpot(s) (cover hole with foil).
Sprinkle black Oreo crumbs on top so no white shows.
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, place clean stem of artificial flower in pot.

title: camarones al mojo de ajo(garlic shrimp)
directions: From underside, split shrimp down the middle without separating them completely.
Carefully spread open.
Remove dark vein if seen.

title: low-fat chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs.
Melt margarine.
Add all ingredients to flour mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serving amount:
2 brownies. Exchanges:
1/2 bread and 1/2 fat.

title: gingerbread cupcakes
directions: Follow cupcake directions on the box.

title: a thankful thanksgiving
directions: Start with a houseful of happiness.
Add a bunch of family and friends.
Next include three hours of eating and sharing food. Throw in three tons of love and kindness.
Mix together with a day full of gathering and sharing conversation.
Leave with one handful of good memories.
Makes one Thankful Thanksgiving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread popped corn on baking sheet; set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Boil 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add baking soda, vanilla and salt. Stir thoroughly; mixture will foam.
Pour over popped corn and mix around well.
Spread out as much as possible.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and bananas.
Add alternately with flour, soda and eggs.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 320° for 1 hour.

title: spice or jam cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in tube pan at 350 degrees until toothpick inserted is clean.

title: pickled beets
directions: Pour over cooked beets and boil 10 minutes.
A little grated horseradish added to beets gives variety.
(Wash beets well, cook, drain water from beets and use in place of plain water.)
The color will be much enhanced.

title: bacardi tropical punch
directions: Mix above ingredients together and chill for 2 hours.
Pour punch over block of ice in punch bowl. Float strawberries and thin slices of oranges, lemons and limes on top.

title: jocelyn's strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, make hoe in center and pour all liquid ingredients in. Mix by hand and pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: biscotti cake
directions: Dip biscottis in milk.
Layer in bottom of large baking dish. Cook pudding according to package directions.
When cooked, add the rum (optional).
Pour pudding over biscottis.
Cool.
When pudding has set, cover pudding with fruit topping and Cool Whip. Can also add slivered almonds, chopped walnuts or shaved chocolate on Cool Whip.

title: ines' rum cake
directions: Combine fat and sugar; cream until very light.
Add eggs; add flour.
Fold in raisins and rum.
Cook in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°. Check cake at 45 minutes.
Bake until mix begins to pull away from the sides of pan and straw pushed into the center of the cake comes out clean.
(Do not overbake.)

title: rice krispy candy
directions: Melt oleo, then add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Press into greased pan.
Cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Transfer to prepared pan.
Bake until top is golden brown and splits slightly, about one hour and twenty minutes.
Serve warm.
Do not double recipe.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Chop beef and cube cheese.
Combine all ingredients, except buttered crumbs, and put into casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: grandma's donuts
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
cup of lukewarm water and add 1 teaspoon
of sugar.
Add shortening and sugar to scalded milk; let cool.
Combine yeast, milk, eggs and dry ingredients.
Let rise until
double;
punch
down.
Roll out and cut out.
Let rise again.
Fry in deep fat at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen donuts.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, add green peppers, mushrooms and onions.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer half the cooked noodles, meat sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Crush cookies.
Combine butter, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip in a bowl. Add pudding.
Sprinkle 1/2 of crushed cookie crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pudding mixture over cookie crumbs, then put remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all. Form into 1-inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased baking sheet. Makes 6 dozen 1-inch balls.

title: shrimp thermidor in casserole
directions: Brown mushrooms in 1/4 cup butter.
Stir flour into 1/3 cup melted butter until smooth.
Gradually add cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Simmer 3 minutes. Add 1/4 cup grated cheese, wine, mustard, cayenne, mushrooms, shrimp and salt.
Mix well.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Melt butter in milk, do not boil.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients.
Beat sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add dry ingredients, alternate milk.
Fold in; add vanilla.

title: orange delicious
directions: Mix in blender, adding ice slowly.

title: apple-raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare two 1/2-inch muffin tins with vegetable pan spray or grease lightly.
(Paper liners won't need oil.)
Mix dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat egg and whip in oil, milk and applesauce.
Add to dry ingredients and mix until flour is moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake for 25 minutes.
Remove from tin immediately.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Mix egg and gelatine; stir over low heat until dissolved.
Mix remaining ingredients with gelatine and egg mixture.
Pour into No Bake or Graham Cracker Pie Crust and sprinkle 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon and 1 teaspoon nutmeg over top.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown onions and ground beef or turkey (microwave; drain well).
Add canned ingredients and seasoning mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in crock-pot and cook.
Top with sour cream, shredded Cheddar and diced green onions.

title: beet jelly
directions: Bring beet juice, Sure-Jell and lemon juice to a hard boil and add sugar, Jell-O and boil 3 to 3 1/2 minutes. Pour in jars like any other jelly.

title: louise's squash dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients and season to taste.
Cook in 350 degrees oven for about one hour.

title: mom's cornbread
directions: Mix sugar and eggs until smooth.
Mix in cornmeal.
Add flour and milk gradually.
Beat until smooth.

title: kriss kringle cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add 3
eggs
and beat well.
Add milk and stir. Gradually add flour,
cream
of tartar, salt and baking soda (sifted together).
Mix and add vanilla.
Chill and roll out on lightly floured	board.	Cut
into
desired shapes. Bake at 400° about 7 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift
flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa. Add
milk and melted shortening, stirring well.
Blend in chopped nuts.
Spread
in
a
9-inch square pan or a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Sprinkle over entire batter and cover with hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, oatmeal, shortening and hot water until smooth. Add eggs and sugar.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to bran mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Blend well; put in gallon jar, cover and refrigerate.
Keep 2 or 3 days before using.
Bake as needed in muffin cups about 25 minutes at 350°.
Will keep in refrigerator about a month.
Makes 60 to 70 muffins.

title: beef cheese casserole
directions: Saute chuck.
Add onion, green pepper and tomato sauce. Simmer and remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream.
Place half of cooked noodles in casserole; cover with half cheese mixture and then remaining noodles and then cheese mixture.
Top with tomato-meat sauce.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven, using 2 to 3-quart casserole.

title: brookens chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In bowl of electric mixer, cream sugar and butter, until soft and fluffy.
Add eggs, all at once. Continue beating, until light.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except pie shell.
Combine well.
Pour into prepared pie crust. Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake about 1 hour, or until pie is firm.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat at medium speed for 2-3 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9 round pan at 350°.
Bake about 20-25 minutes.

title: pistachio nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O pudding in crushed pineapple (juice and all). Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and chopped nuts.
Make up a day ahead. Serves 10.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Saute onion, peppers and mushrooms in olive and oleo combination.
Add shrimp, parsley, lemon pepper and garlic powder. Add a bit of low-fat milk and yogurt.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sweet potato bran bread
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients until moistened.
Place in muffin tins or greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Yields 1 loaf or 12 muffins.

title: fried doves
directions: Combine milk, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce. Add dove breast and marinate 12 hours in refrigerator. Milk mixture should cover the breast. Drain and salt and pepper; roll in flour to coat. Fry until golden brown.

title: hunter's stew(bigos)
directions: In a large heavy skillet or Dutch oven, brown stew meat in olive oil over medium heat. Reduce heat to low and add garlic and onion; cook until onion is clear.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve with boiled potatoes and heavy bread and sliced Edam cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a 3-quart baking dish.
Mix in crumbled bread.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread the pineapple (juice included) in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Next, spoon the cherry pie filling on top; sprinkle the dry cake mix over this.
Spread pecans over this; dot with margarine. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: play dough("dough it yourself")
directions: In
a
large
bowl,
mix flour, salt and alum together. Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, bring the water and oil to a boil. Remove
from
heat
and
pour over flour mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Knead the dough.
Color the dough by adding a few drops of food coloring.
Store in a covered container.

title: croquette
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender.
Mash potatoes and mix with milk.
Fry ground beef and onion with salt and pepper.
Mix mashed potatoes with ground beef and make flat oblong shaped patties.
Roll patties in flour and dip in egg.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Deep fry until brown.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and Jell-O and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with marshmallows. Mix cake according to directions on box and pour over rhubarb and marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake tests done with a toothpick. Serve warm or cold with a drop of Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Combine mushroom soup and cooked broccoli.
Add French fried onions, cream cheese, water chestnuts, chunk chicken and chopped onion.
Put in a casserole dish.
Combine Ritz cracker crumbs and margarine; put this on top of casserole. Place in oven and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: pollo con cipolla (onion) and red roasted peppers
directions: In a large frypan heat the oil, add onion, garlic and red pepper and gently fry for 10 minutes.
Add the chicken pieces, salt and pepper and fry until browned on both sides.
Mix the tomato paste with a little water and stir into the pan; add wine and cook on low for about 10 minutes, covered.
Chop one sprig of rosemary and sprinkle over chicken.
Cook another few minutes until chicken is tender, adding a little of the stock to moisten. Transfer to serving dish and garnish with rosemary.
Serves 4.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix a dressing by mixing the ranch dressing and the cocktail sauce together. Go a little heavier on the amount of ranch dressing than the cocktail sauce when mixing. Mix all the other ingredients together and then mix the sauce into the mixture thoroughly. Chill overnight. Serve over your favorite greens.

title: green bean and mushroom soup
directions: Heat green beans, soup and milk.
Mix in onion rings.
Pour into casserole and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: jello strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Let cool slightly.
Add pineapple and chopped bananas and strawberries.
Place half of mixture in large dish.
Let chill until firm.
Mix 1 box Jell-O cheesecake mix, spread over chilled Jell-O.
Add the remaining half of Jell-O, let chill until firm.
Add Cool Whip.

title: chocolate divine dessert
directions: Place almonds on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until light brown.
Watch carefully so almonds do not burn.
Cool and set aside.
In top of double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate chips with sugar.
Cool.
Mix in beaten egg yolks. Gradually fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla.
Tear up angel food cake into 1/2-inch pieces. Put half of cake pieces on bottom of buttered 10-inch spring-form pan.
Cover with half of chocolate mixture.
Layer remaining cake and chocolate.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Remove rim.
Top with toasted almonds.
May be made up to 3 days in advance.

title: cheese logs
directions: Mix in large bowl all ingredients except cream cheese.
Blend well.
Add cream cheese until texture is malleable.
Careful not to overwork mixture.
If mixture gets squishy, chill until workable.

title: stir-fried chicken and rice
directions: In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of corn oil over medium high heat.
Add broccoli, carrots, walnuts and garlic.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove vegetables.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons corn oil to skillet.
Add chicken.
Stir-fry 1 minute or until chicken turns white.
Add soy sauce, sherry, ginger root and sugar. Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon.
Add broth and green onions to skillet and bring to a boil.
Stir in chicken and vegetables mixture.
Remove from heat.
Let stand covered about 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, it will have a biscuit dough consistency. Pour into a greased or sprayed loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes in a preheated oven. Great with roasts, steaks or standing rib roasts.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Layer 12 sandwiches on the bottom of the casserole dish. Spread half the Cool Whip evenly over the sandwiches.
Sprinkle 3 of the crushed candy bars over the Cool Whip.
Drizzle chocolate syrup on top.
Layer the remainder of the ingredients in the same order and place in the freezer 24 hours ahead of time.
Take out of the freezer at the beginning of your meal.

title: frozen cream cups
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until smooth; blend in sugar, then whipping cream and vanilla.
Pour into paper-lined (foil) muffin tins and freeze.
Remove foil liners and spoon fruit over top. These will keep in freezer several months.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Boil eggs to hard boiled stage and chop finely.
Chop sweet pickles and pimentos into fine pieces.
Grate cheese.
Mix together all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate.

title: almond tartlets
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Cream the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in the egg.
Add the lemon juice and fold in the flour and ground almonds.
Pipe or spoon into the pastry shells, filling each one to just below the top. Scatter with the slivered almonds and bake for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from the oven and brush the tops with hot apricot jam.

title: stack cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients. Cream butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and milk. Add flour mixture to form a workable dough. Divide dough into 4 parts. Roll each part and cut out circle with pie pan or around a plate. Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° until lightly browned. Place desired fruit between layers. Serves 8 to 10.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust)
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well
after
each.
Add milk and flour, blending well. Add coconut;
mix.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: date squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour and baking powder, which have been sifted together.
Add vanilla, then dates and nuts.
Put into a well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan, spreading thin enough to cover bottom of the pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while still warm.
Makes about 25 squares.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Add milk gradually and continue beating.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat into egg mixture.
Add melted butter and coconut.
Bake in two 8-inch pie pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(This pie makes its own crust.)

title: sauce diable(great with leftover beef or pork)
directions: Cook consomme until reduced to 1 cup.
Melt butter and saute onions.
Mix in flour, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, lemon juice and mustard.
Mix in reduced consomme and heat through. Pour over meat* and garnish with green onions.

title: fred harvey cole slaw
directions: Pour over cabbage; do not stir.
Let set at least 4 hours. Toss and serve.
Keeps well.

title: banana split pizza
directions: Mix brownie mix, adding 1 extra egg.
Bake and cool completely. Mix together the cream cheese and sugar; whip and fold in pineapple.
Spread on top of brownie.
Refrigerate.
Top with fruit of choice:
bananas, strawberries, chopped nuts and/or shredded coconut.
Drizzle with Hershey's syrup.
Eat within 24 hours.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with sugar.
Add eggs and last add flour with soda and baking powder.
Bake in greased and floured pan in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar, milk and peanut butter together until creamy and smooth.
Gradually add Cool Whip until well blended.
Then put in a baked pie shell and chill.
Decorate with peanut butter chips.

title: peppered beef tenderloin
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Pour into pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hello dollys
directions: Layer in
order of recipe; do not stir or mix.	Use 8 x 8-inch or	9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (less for glass pans).

title: rice stuffed zucchini rounds
directions: To Prepare Zucchini Rounds:
Trim ends from zucchini; do not peel.
Cut into 2-inch crosswise slices.
Cook in boiling salted water until fork-tender.
Do not overcook.
Cool.
Using melon baller or teaspoon, hollow out center part of zucchini, leaving 1/4-inch shell on bottom and sides.
Discard seeds and pulp. Drain, hollow side down, on paper towels until ready to use.
Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly butter bottom only of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: mother's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake about 15 minutes and turn down to 350° about 30 more minutes.

title: bacon and green chili cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and garlic powder.
Add buttermilk and eggs; stir well.
Stir in bacon, onions and chilies.
Place shortening in 10-inch skillet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Great with soups!

title: cream soup substitute mix(makes nine 10 ounce cans of soup)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium bowl and store in airtight container.
To substitute one 10 3/4 ounce can of cream soup, use 1/3 cup
mix plus 1 1/4 cups water.
Combine in a medium saucepan and cook until thick.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Cut orange in pieces (include peel) and grind in blender.
Add apples and cranberries; grind.
Add sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Put mixture in sterilized 1/2 pint jars and refrigerate.
Stores up to one month in refrigerator.

title: baked vegetable dinner
directions: In the bottom of a small roaster, put a layer of sliced potatoes, a layer of carrots and a layer of onions and celery, mixed.
Brown ground beef and layer this over celery and onions. Pour can of peas (juice and all) over this.
Over the top, put 2 cans of tomatoes; salt and pepper each layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Remove the lid and bake 1/2 hour longer.
Do not add any water as the vegetables make their own juice.

title: maggie's baked beans
directions: Saute onions.
Cut sausage in 1/2-inch slices, then into halves.
Brown sausage in onions.
Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, uncovered.
Serves 24.

title: ravioli with vegetables and pesto
directions: Saute the vegetables until crisp-tender.
Stir into ravioli and pesto sauce.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs and 1 stick margarine.
Press in a 12 x 18-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt and put in an ungreased 9-inch pan about 2 to 2 1/2 inches deep.
Make three (3) indentations with a spoon.
In one indentation put vanilla.
In the second indentation put the vinegar.
In the third indentation put the melted shortening. Mix all together with a fork, but do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chilled spiced cider
directions: In a large saucepan, combine apple juice or cider, cinnamon sticks and the orange peel, cut in a long spiral and stuffed with whole cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Skim froth and chill well.
Makes about sixteen 4-ounce servings.

title: custard cream pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend at medium speed for 4 minutes.
If you desire coconut cream pie, add the coconut now. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in water for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix, adding pecans last.
Put in pastry shell and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and chicken together.
Then crumble crackers on top of mixture.
Cook in oven at 350° until crackers are brown.

title: catherine's favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and pour off fat.
Simmer everything 2 hours.
Add 1/3 cup red wine.
Add Ragu spaghetti sauce with mushrooms. Simmer 1 hour more.

title: potato candy
directions: Use a small peeled potato or if using a large potato, cut it down to the size of a golf ball (about 1/4 cup).
Boil potato until done.
Then drain and put in a bowl.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken, fruit and celery; chill.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except for cashews. Chill. Just before serving, combine chicken mixture, dressing and cashews.
Serve in hollowed out pineapple shells or on lettuce leaves.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Slice pork in thin, bite-size pieces.
Cook in 3-quart saucepan in hot oil until brown.
Remove pork and set aside.
In same pan, bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add pork, bamboo shoots, bean sprouts and mushrooms.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add vinegar, soy sauce and pepper.
Blend cornstarch in cold water.
Stir into soup, stirring until slightly thickened.
Continue stirring and add egg.
Garnish with onions and serve.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter.
Add extract and blend until smooth.
Slowly add powdered sugar until of spreading consistency.

title: sweet pickle
directions: Wash cukes and cut into chunks (1 gallon of chunks).
Boil 1 gallon water with 2 cups salt.
Pour over cucumbers in crock jar or plastic bucket.
Weigh down.
Let set 8 days.
Drain and rinse well.
Cover with 2 ounces of alum per gallon of boiling water. Let set for 24 hours.
Drain and rinse (once).
Cover with apple cider vinegar.
Let set 8 to 24 hours.
Drain.
Layer: pickle, sugar and spice (use 10 pounds of sugar to 4 gallons of pickles). Let stand 2 days (makes its own syrup).
Stir.
Let stand 2 or 3 more days.
Can or leave in crock.

title: chocolate ecstasy
directions: Bake and cool cake.
Prepare pudding per package directions. Layer 1/2 cake, cut in 1 1/2-inch squares, 1/4 cup Kahlua (pour over cake) and 1/2 pudding spread over cake, then 1/2 Cool Whip and 2 Heath bars, crushed.
Repeat.
Chill and serve.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While still hot, spread 1 small jar marshmallow cream on top, then pour icing on top.

title: pineapple zucchini
directions: Combine the 4 ingredients in large container.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, put in large pot.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Cool; put into freezer containers.
Freeze or you may can it.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut the tops off the bell peppers; clean and set aside.
Using the pepper that you cut off around the stem, chop this, onion and garlic; add to ground beef, rice, egg, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In a large pot, bring several quarts of water to a rolling boil.
Drop your bell peppers in the boiling water until peppers change color of green.
Remove with tongs and fill with stuffing mixture.
Place peppers in baking dish with 1/2 inch water in dish.
Cover top of stuffing with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, or until mixture is done.

title: new york style cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons butter together and blend well.
Reserve 2 tablespoons for warmth. Press in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill while preparing filling.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Beat egg and milk together. Add oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 8-inch square pan in a 450° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in mixing bowl. Cut in shortening with pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add milk and blend lightly with a fork until flour is moistened and dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead lightly for 30 seconds.
Roll 3/4 inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter. Place close together on lightly greased baking pan.
Brush tops of biscuits with butter or margarine.
Bake at 475° (very hot oven) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 16 biscuits.

title: fudge
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Combine in a bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Stir into mixture the butter, soda, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and flour to form a soft ball.
On a floured surface, pat dough to 3/4-inch thickness. Cut with a 2 1/2-inch floured doughnut cutter.
In electric skillet, heat 1 inch of oil to 350°.
Fry 2 minutes per side.
Dip tops into frosting or coat with sugar.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, but not mushy; cool. Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon in a medium saucepan.
Stir in the apricot nectar, hot water and orange peel; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in the butter. Cool slightly. Stir in pecans.
Cut potatoes in half or smaller pieces and place in 7 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish. Pour sauce over potatoes so all are glazed. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes or until sauce is bubbly. Serves 8.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop or puree spinach.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Top with sour cream just before serving.
Serve with crackers or small slices of rye bread.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove bone from salmon.
Mash salmon in its own liquid and combine with other ingredients.
Baked in shallow, 8 x 8-inch baking dish at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until firmly set and slightly puffy.

title: wilma's vegetable salad
directions: Add salt, pepper and dill or oregano to taste.

title: pineapple cheese cake(diet dessert)
directions: Pour evaporated milk in a large mixing bowl and freeze until crystals form when whipped.
Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Then mash with fork until creamy.
Pour pineapple juice into a cup, adding water to equal 1 cup of juice and water. Dissolve gelatin in boiling juice; cool.
Add cream cheese and vanilla; beat well.
Fold in pineapple and whipped milk.
Line bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Fill with mixture and refrigerate.
Cut into 12 servings.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook in covered skillet on medium-high until chicken is brown.
Pour off excess grease.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken in skillet.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast until dissolved.
Add melted shortening, sugar, salt and beaten eggs.
Stir in flour (will be very sticky). Pour into a large greased bowl.
Let rise double in size (2 to 3 hours).
Pour onto floured board and knead in flour (not too much).
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased pans; let rise for about 1 1/2 hours. Heat oven to 350° and bake about 20 minutes until brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt.
Dip in any fruit that you like.

title: igloo cake
directions: Bake a two-layer cake in round baking pans.
Cool thoroughly and cut each layer in half.
Use canned frosting or make your own. Spread frosting on one side of three halves.
Set halves side by side, on cut edges, with icing between to form a long, rounded cake which makes the igloo.
Frost remaining cake.

title: potluck potato casserole
directions: Mix together the 1/2 cup margarine, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Add thawed potatoes and blend carefully. Pour mixture into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Mix 1/4 cup melted margarine and corn flakes together and sprinkle over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix
together strawberry jello and frozen strawberries.
Mix together with dry ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix the ingredients and make into balls.
Let chill.
Melt in microwave a 12 ounce package chocolate chips.
Dip candy balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in boiling water until tender. Drain.
Saute onion and celery in the 2 tablespoons bacon fat. Combine all ingredients except cheese and parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Garnish each serving with Cheddar cheese and parsley.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg. Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. In separate bowl, beat sugar, 3 eggs and vanilla together. Pour over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 325° and bake an additional 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pearl barnes' fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and margarine.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to mixture.
Mix well; add fruit cocktail and all juice.
Pour into greased and floured oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread on batter
in pan, 1/2 cup coconut.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; then bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: no-mix cherry supreme
directions: Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk together.
Pour over melted butter; do not stir.
Pour pie filling over mixture; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Cook down 1 1/2 hours to a greasy- looking skim.
Add 1 c. vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes more.
Put in jars and seal.

title: cris' macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to instructions.
After draining off boiling water, put back in pot and let sit in cold water for 5 minutes, drain well.
Pour the juice from 1 small jar of olives or 1/2 large jar over macaroni and mix.
Dice olives (about 3 slices each), onion, celery and green pepper.
Add to macaroni.
(If using tuna, omit green pepper; add other vegetables and mix, then add tuna and mix.)
Add celery seed according to your preference; mix well.
Add 5 to 6 tablespoons of Miracle Whip (more or less to your preference).
Mix very well.
Chill approximately 1 hour and serve.

title: lo-cal spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. To serve, stir 1 teaspoon mix into 5 ounce cup of boiling water.

title: green tomato supreme
directions: Use in equal amounts the onions, green tomatoes and green sweet peppers.

title: malt shoppe pie
directions: Combine softened ice cream and whipped topping until well blended.
Reserve 8 whole Whoppers for garnish. Crush remaining Whoppers. Add 1 cup of crushed candy to ice cream mixture; reserve remaining 1/2 cup.
Spoon ice cream mixture into pie crust. Top pie with remaining 1/2 cup candy and freeze 4 hours.
To serve, garnish with whipped topping and 8 Whoppers.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter cheese fudge
directions: In microwave safe bowl, heat butter, cheese and peanut butter for 30 seconds.
Stir and heat for another 30 seconds, until nearly melted.
Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Spread in 9x12x2 pan.
Make 3 3/4 lbs.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion, celery and garlic in same oil very slowly for 15 minutes.
Do not allow to brown.
Return chicken to pan and add remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes. Serve over freshly cooked mostaccioli.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream 1 cup Crisco with 2 1/4 cups of the sugar until creamy. Add egg yolks, then buttermilk, then flour, soda and salt.
Beat until creamy.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and add the remaining sugar.
Beat until peaks form.
Fold egg whites into cake batter.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven door before time is up or cake will fall!

title: pneumonia remedy
directions: Melt lard and set off stove.
Add camphor gum cut fine.
Stir to dissolve.
Add kerosene, turpentine and ammonia.
Stir until cool.
Rub on the chest and back if you have a deep cough.
I had this 50 years.

title: jill's overnight oatmeal pancakes
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine oatmeal and buttermilk. Stir well, cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix beef, salt, pepper and flour.
Saute onion in oleo; do not brown, then add beef mixture and stir over low heat until meat turns a gray color.
Add undiluted soup, mushrooms and chestnuts, cooking about 6 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Serve over rice.
This freezes well, but when reheating, do not allow mixture to come to a boil.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt the chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat; gradually blend in milk.
Mix the sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Combine coconut and nuts; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until puffed and browned.
(Filling will be soft, but will set while cooling.)
Cool at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: antoine's chicken casserole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Season chicken with salt and pepper and brown.
Remove chicken to a plate.
Add butter or margarine to oil in skillet.
Stir in flour and make a dark roux. (With heat at medium setting, stir flour and oil until flour turns a dark, reddish brown.
Do not burn.
Start roux over if you smell burning or see smoke.)
Add all other ingredients, except wine. Stir, off heat, until well mixed.
Stir, adding wine, until mixture is smooth.
Return to low heat.
Add chicken and simmer, covered, for about 45 minutes.
If sauce is thin, simmer uncovered until it thickens.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn-cheese pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: red pea soup
directions: Soak meat to remove excess salt.
Wash peas.
Cook meat and peas in 2 quarts of water until both are soft.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Add dumplings at your final 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add the remainder of ingredients and mix well.
Makes 3 loaves.
Grease and flour loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with soft cream cheese mixed with any preserves or jam that will complement your bread.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together except crackers and oleo.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt oleo and mix with crumbled crackers; spread over top of Veg-All mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: beet salad
directions: If julienne beets are used, chop a bit as they drain.

title: colonial cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Sprinkle in and beat sugar a little at a time.

title: ann's potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in well-greased casserole. Top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Add another 1/8 cup melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Don't neglect the horseradish.
It gives this dip a nice "bite."
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: squash casserole(south of the border)
directions: Cut squash into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine first 4 ingredients in 1-quart saucepan; cook 6 to 8 minutes or until squash is tender.
Drain well.
Add chilies, pimiento and cheese.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Place egg slices on top and sprinkle with corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until casserole is thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: irish soda bread(scone)
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a wooden spoon until well mixed.
Grease a tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
In bacon grease, brown onions over low heat.
Add chopped green pepper and okra; thicken with flour.
Add water, stirring constantly to keep lumps out.
Cook for about 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients, except shrimp and bacon; cook slowly for 15 or 20 minutes.
Add more water, if needed.
Add shrimp and crumbled bacon; cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 average servings.

title: brazilian black beans(feijoada completa)
directions: Heat the oil in a large, heavy deep pot and stir-fry the onion and garlic for 1 minute or until light golden brown.
Add the beans, salt pork, Portuguese sausage, ham hocks, corned beef, salt, black pepper, bay leaves, halved orange and water.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until the beans are tender, stirring occasionally and adding water if needed.
Serve with sliced oranges, Manioc Meal with butter and eggs, Brazilian Rice, Collard Greens, Vinaigrette Sauce and Cachaca Cocktail.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry supreme cake
directions: Combine cake mix, gelatin, oil, eggs, 3/4 of the package strawberries and 1/4 cup water in electric mixer bowl; mix until light and creamy.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: cheese balls with olives
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients (except olives) well with hands.
Form into balls.
Place olive inside of ball.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine the sour cream and mayonnaise.
Boil the spinach until separated.
Then when finished, strain until no water is left. Put drained spinach in same bowl as the sour cream and mayonnaise. Chop the chestnuts and put them in the same bowl.
Add the package of leek onion soup mix.
Now mix with wire whisk.
Now set in refrigerator with foil over the top.
Hollow out the round loaf of bread.
Cut the long loaf of bread into bite-size pieces.
Put spinach dip in the hollowed out round loaf when ready to serve.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine oats, flour, brown sugar and margarine and make a crumbly mixture.
Make 1 layer of half of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Sprinkle rest of oat mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until brown.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli mixture and chill.

title: caramel rice krispies
directions: In a bowl, melt 1 1/2 sticks butter and the caramels in the microwave. Add sweetened condensed milk and blend well. Set aside. In a large pan, melt 6 Tbsp. butter, add marshmallows and melt completely. Add Rice Krispies and mix well. Stir, again, the caramel mixture, you may even have to microwave it again for a couple seconds. Add it to the Rice Krispies and mix well. Using buttered spatula, press into 2 13 x 9 inch pans.

title: chicken pilou
directions: Mix chicken and all seasonings together.
Preheat Dutch oven pot, covering the bottom with cooking oil.
Place the sugar in the center of the pot.
Allow the sugar to brown to a caramel color, then stir and mix with the oil.
Add the chicken; saute until chicken is almost tender.
Add enough water to cover chicken about 2 inches above.
Now, add rice and stir.
The amount of rice should be half water, half rice.
You can check this by dipping the spoon in the pot and pulling it out and observe the amount of water and rice.
Continue to add rice until there is half rice and half water in the spoon.
Simmer until rice is absorbed and fluffy.
Stir occasionally, folding the rice from the sides of the pan inward. Cover and simmer over very low heat.

title: broccoli stem - marinade
directions: Peel broccoli stems and slice thin.
Combine remaining ingredients to make marinade. Pour marinade over broccoli stems. Marinate 6 hours.
Very good and crunchy in salads.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Melt butter in skillet; add ground beef and cook until brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.

title: orange buttermilk muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Beat egg into mixture. In blender, add orange with peel and buttermilk; whack up into small pieces.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix thoroughly.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not use muffin papers.

title: 5 minute pie
directions: Mix eagle brand
milk and lemon juice.
Now add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crust, sprinkle with pecans.
Best if made the day before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine oil and sugar; add grated carrots.
Add eggs and mix well; sift together flour and cinnamon and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese roll
directions: Mix and chill.
Roll into cheese roll or ball, finish by rolling in reserved nuts.

title: hash brown cheese potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup, sauce, garlic and onion in a bowl.
Mix well. In a greased casserole, place a layer of corn chips and alternate with chicken mixture, cheese and broth.
Have chips and cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini omelet
directions: Saute onion in butter and oil until soft; do not brown.
Pare and slice zucchini very thin.
Add to sauteed onion.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes, until zucchini is golden brown.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Bring jello, water and crushed pineapple to a boil; let cool. Add Dream Whip or Cool Whip, cottage cheese, nuts or frozen strawberries, if desired, or both.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown together ground beef and sausage.
Cut Velveeta cheese in pieces and stir in browned meat.
Stir and heat until cheese is melted.
Spread on 1/2 mini bagels and bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in 1-quart bowl, covered with 1/2 cup water, 8 to 10 minutes on high.
Set aside.
Arrange layers of carrots, sliced onions and pepper in 1-quart bowl; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in another bowl.
Cover and bring to a boil, about 5 minutes on high.
Stir several times to blend.
Pour over layered vegetables.
Cool and refrigerate until serving time.

title: coconut mounds bars
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter and powdered sugar. Pat into a 9 x 13 pan and bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: saucepan hollandaise
directions: In a small heavy saucepan, combine egg yolks and lemon juice. Blend until smooth, using a wooden spoon or rubber scraper.
Add 1/2 stick butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter is melted.
Add remaining butter and continue stirring until melted.
Add boiling water, a tablespoon at a time, and blend.
Continue cooking and stirring until sauce is thickened. Remove from heat immediately.
Season with salt, pepper and cayenne.
If sauce is refrigerated, it may be reheated in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Serves 8.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and spices.
Cream butter and sugar. Stir soda into applesauce.
Add egg.
Combine with the creamed mixture.
Gradually mix in sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons, two or three inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix ingredients and dip wieners and deep fry in hot oil.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, drain & mash. Add all ingredients except oleo & cracker crumbs. Put into a 2 qt. casserole & top with crumbs & oleo. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: tomato slush
directions: In glass container, combine all ingredients.
Cover.
Freeze until slush consistency, approximately 4 hours.
Spoon into serving glasses. Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except 7-Up.
Just before serving, add 7-Up.
Makes about 40 cups.
Pour over crushed ice.

title: quick cheese cake
directions: Cream all ingredients
in
order;
pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for
35 minutes.
Top with favorite fruit topping or serve plain.

title: kentucky lemon pie
directions: Mix and pour in shell.	Cook
on
lower
shelf	of oven about 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Put beans in an 8 to 10-quart pot.
Add enough cold water to cover the beans.
Add onion and garlic and bring to a boil.
Cook 1 hour, then add all the other things and more (hot) water if necessary.
Simmer for 2 hours or until beans are soft.
Remove 2 cups of beans without juice and mash very good.
Return to pot and stir.
Add more water if you like lots of juice.
Always use hot water to add.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil, then add dry ingredients.
Add zucchini, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: oyster with eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water to cover in 2-quart saucepan until tender.
Add onion; cook for 3 minutes longer.
Drain. Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine beaten egg yolks, milk and cream in bowl; fold into eggplant.
Fold butter and cracker crumbs into stiffly beaten egg whites; stir into eggplant mixture with half the oysters.
Arrange remaining oysters on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: glitter cookies
directions: Beat together sugars, margarine and oil until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix. Chill overnight.
Roll into small ball.
Flatten and sprinkle colored sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in sugar and oats.
Mix buttermilk, egg and oil.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 425 degrees for 18-20 minutes.
(Apples or raisins can be substituted for blueberries.)

title: chili egg puff
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and melted butter.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in chiles.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until top is brown and center firm.
Serves 4 people.
Breakfast or lunch.

title: "just like grandma's" sugary popcorn
directions: Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add popcorn and sugar.
Cover and shake over medium heat until the popcorn stops popping.
Shake well as it will burn easily.
Yield: 11 cups.

title: southern rice pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, raisins, water, sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in rice.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 2 minutes; stir well.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Cover; microwave at Medium-low 10 minutes; stir well.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Cover; microwave at Medium-low 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Toss lightly and put into baking dish.
Put chips, then cheese over top.
Bake in hot (400°) oven for 15 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Place in saucepan and stir over low heat until dissolved, sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cook ingredients without stirring over medium heat to the hard crack stage (290°).

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix with water, eggs, oil and 1 can of the coconut. Beat 2 minutes.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
As soon as cake is taken out of oven poke holes all over the top. Pour the cream of coconut over the top and cool.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: celery casserole
directions: Place in order given.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
A very good side dish for stuffing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop the cranberries and pour sugar over them. Let them set while the Jell-O thickens. Add all other ingredients to Jell-O mixture and pour into a mold or dish. Chill until firm.

title: sweet and salsa meat balls
directions: Combine the 2 sauces well and heat until blended.
Pour over precooked meat, heat a little longer and serve.
It is Mm Mm good!

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in long baking dish, 9 x 12 x 2-inch.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk together.
Pour batter over melted butter and carefully put peaches on top of batter.
Do not stir. Bake at 375° until lightly browned, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour, potato chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat and drain well. Add seasoning and fry down until onions are clear. Add beans and sauce with the brown sugar. Once this starts to cook and is almost done, add syrup (go around the pot about 3 times).

title: late-night breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a shallow bowl, combine the first five ingredients; set aside.
Divide dough into 16 pieces; roll each into a 6 inch rope.
Dip ropes in butter, then roll in cheese mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Let rest for 10 minutes.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add all ingredients except for 1/3 bottle of dressing.
Let sit overnight.
Add remaining dressing before serving.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Combine boiling water, dry soup and rice.
Let come to a boil. Boil 7 minutes on medium heat. Add sausage and remainder of ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
If mixture seems too dry, add a little water as it cooks.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in sheet cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together the first five ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together, then pour over tossed ingredients and mix together just before serving.

title: broiled fish
directions: Pat fish dry with paper towels.
Combine cornmeal, flour, paprika, salt and pepper in a flat dish.
Place oil in baking dish.
Heat in 425° oven 1 minute.
Dredge fish in cornmeal mixture; shake off excess.
Arrange fish pieces 1 inch apart. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425°, allowing 10 minutes per inch thickness or until fish flakes when tested with a fork. Yields 4 servings.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients, then add oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Shape into rolls and chill thoroughly or overnight.
Slice and bake in a 375° oven until golden brown.

title: nut rolls
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread chopped nuts in pan.
Arrange rolls on pecans.
Mix granulated sugar, ground sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle mixture over rolls.
Cover with foil and damp towel.
Let mixture rise overnight in oven.
Remove damp towel.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until rolls are lightly browned.
Remove from oven and let sit for 5 minutes.
Turn upside down on tray.

title: hot fudge sunday cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and baking powder; stir in milk, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cherry oatmeal pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, oats and margarine with fork (save the desired amount for top of pie).
Press into 9-inch pie plate on sides and bottom.
Add cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle with reserved oatmeal mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Drain three or more cans of sliced water chestnuts.
Cut bacon long enough to wrap around chestnuts.
Wrap bacon around chestnuts and fasten with a toothpick.
Bake at 400° until bacon is done.
Drain grease.
Make sauce of equal amounts of white sugar and catsup (one cup of each).
Heat until sugar is melted.
Pour over chestnuts.

title: terry's terrific taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1/2 jar of salsa.
If you enjoy really spicy foods, add cayenne pepper, chili powder and cumin to taste. Spread mixture evenly in bottom of quiche dish.
Spread remaining salsa over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle on top; chopped red and green pepper, chopped green onion, chopped tomato and sliced black olives.
Serve as a dip with nacho chips.
Enjoy!

title: taco casserole
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet until beef loses redness; drain fat.
