Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and water; simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake in a 350°oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Put melted butter and sugar in bread pan (8 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 3-inch).
Sprinkle with water.
Divide dough into 3 equal parts. Roll each underhand to long roll 1-inch in diameter.
Braid and place in pan.
Brush with milk.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix all together.
Heat small amount of cooking oil on medium heat.
Spoon out mixture into small patties.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, vanilla and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in peanut butter, then sifted dry ingredients.
Form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with prongs of fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for about ten minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: stuffed peppers(best in the west)
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Parboil 5 minutes; drain. Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in rice and 3/4 cup Cheez Whiz and tomatoes.
Fill peppers.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with rest of cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: make it light - pumpkin cheesecake delight
directions: Coat bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan with cooking spray. Wrap outside, bottom and sides of pan with aluminum foil.
In food processor, add Ricotta and cream cheese and process until smooth. Add next 7 ingredients and process until smooth.
Pour into large bowl; stir in pumpkin and set aside.
Beat 4 egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar (1 tablespoon at a time); beat until soft peaks form.
Gently stir in 1/4 of egg mixture into pumpkin mix.
Continue to fold in remaining egg white mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Place in a large shallow pan.
Add hot water to larger pan to depth of about 1-inch.
Bake at 300° for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Remove foil from outside of spring-form pan.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Serve with fresh whipped cream or Cool Whip on top of each serving!
Yields 12 servings (approximately 233 calories per serving; 7 g. of fat).

title: "junk"
directions: Will also need 1 garbage bag.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix the ingredients in a pan on the stove over low heat and warm thoroughly.
Stir slowly and it makes a good dip for Doritoes, etc.
It's very good with a Mexican dinner or anytime.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs, then add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: dark chocolate raspberry cheesecake
directions: In food processor, blend wafers, sugar and pecans until finely chopped.
Put in small bowl.
Add melted butter and stir until well combined.
Grease bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan and press crumbs evenly on the bottom.
Chill.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Fry onion until tender in 3 tablespoons bacon fat.
Add water and diced potatoes and cook until potatoes are tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Add cream-style corn, corn, milk and seasonings.
Heat to piping hot.
Add pat of butter.
Put some crumbled bacon in chowder; reserve the remainder to sprinkle on top, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: 1-2-3 cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix peanut butter, butter, sugar and boiling water.
Blend with beater/mixer until smooth.
Stir in Bisquick.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set, but not hard.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: zuni stew
directions: Cook meat in water until done.
Add the vegetables and simmer 2 hours.
Serve with Indian Fry Bread.

title: carnival punch
directions: Place lemon, lime, orange, pineapple or raspberry sherbet in a large punch bowl.
Chill.

title: richest cake in the world
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Pour butterscotch topping over cake.
Put Cool Whip over all.
Sprinkle bits of candy over Cool Whip.
Eat and enjoy!

title: chop suey
directions: Cut pork and beef fine and brown slightly.
Add celery and onion.
Cover with water.
Season with salt and simmer for about 45 minutes.
Add soy sauce, Fuji sauce and molasses.
Cook until meat is fork-tender.
Then add bean sprouts just before thickening with 2 tablespoons cornstarch moistened in cold water.

title: snowball kisses
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add flour and pecans. Chill 1/2 hour.
Shape dough around Kiss just enough to cover Kiss.
Roll into a ball.
Bake in preheated 375° oven on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
May roll in powdered sugar, if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: mexican squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain well.
Mix in cheese and green chilies.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: beno's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour either Bundt or tube pan.
Sift flour 3 times.
Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs one at a time, beating in each egg until mixture is lemon color.
Add flour slowly.
Add vanilla.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top lightly springs back and/or straw inserted in middle comes up clean.
There is no leavening agent.
Secret to good cake is beating each egg enough.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick Pam or grease with 3 teaspoons of olive oil on medium to medium-high heat.
Slowly saute chicken with onion and pepper for 30 minutes, turning chicken once.
Drain off fat.
Add salsa.
Cover skillet and turn heat down to medium-low and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice and garnish with sour cream.
Makes 5 servings.

title: moist 'n crispy onion chicken
directions: Place onion soup mix and bread crumbs in large plastic food bag and shake to blend.
Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Place chicken, one piece at a time, in the bag. Close tightly and shake until well coated.
Place chicken on a rack in broiler pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
For more onion flavor, use 2 packages of onion soup and reduce bread crumbs to 1/3 cup.

title: maine baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Cover with water; parboil until skins break.
Mix sugar, molasses, etc. together.
Pour over beans and liquid in a 4-quart bean pot.
Cut pork into squares almost to the rind and place on top.
Bake at 325° for approximately 6 hours.
Check and add water when needed.

title: lemon angel food cake
directions: Take 1 lemon angel food cake and slice into four layers.
Mix lemon pudding and lemon yogurt; spread between layers.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: all american stew
directions: Cut meat and vegetables into serving sizes.
Mix tomato sauce, tapioca, sugar and salt.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake about 4 hours in slow oven at 250° (cover).
Serves 6 or 7.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Melt butter and mix in nuts.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, cream or tartar or corn syrup and water into a pot.
Cook at low heat.
Stir until well mixed.
Beat at high speed for 1 minute with an electric mixer.
Beat on low speed for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla; beat until it stands in peaks.
Spread on cool cake between layers and sprinkle coconut on top.

title: strawberries
directions: You will need round green toothpicks.

title: chicken jubilee
directions: Place chicken breast halves in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine chili sauce, onion, raisins, water, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chicken, cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. Combine Bing cherries and sherry.
At the end of 45 minutes, pour mixture over chicken. Cover and continue baking for 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg.
At low speed, beat until stiff dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Immediately top each cookie with candy kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around the edge.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and oil until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; add dry ingredients and roll in sugar in small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with glass.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; drain.
Add remaining items and mix well.
Heat and serve on a bun.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Put some sugar in a bowl and roll a teaspoonful of dough in it at a time.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: red chile salsa
directions: Mix ingredients and serve!

title: easy nachos
directions: Place about 3 dozen tortilla chips on an ungreased baking sheet.
Spread 2 teaspoons refried beans on each chip.
Sprinkle with green onions and cheese.
Top each with a slice of jalapeno pepper.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix on high speed until smooth.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: hot chocolate supreme
directions: Combine both ingredients in a medium saucepan; stir over low heat until hot and smooth.

title: nancy's 6-bean casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Add soup, mustard, paste and sugar.
Cool 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over beans.
Stir and bake for 1 hour at 350° in large casserole dish.
(Drain all except chili, kidney and pork and beans.)

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Refrigerate until served.

title: shell bark cake
directions: Beat until fluffy, shortening and sugar.
Then add eggs and beat
until
creamy.
Sift together, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add	milk
and
dry ingredients, alternately.
Add vanilla and cut up nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: alaska apple butter
directions: Soak apples and water together for 1 hour.
Add cranberries and cook until soft.
Put pulp through food sieve.
Reheat and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until clear.
Add juice and grated rind of lemon.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: artichoke and spinach casserole
directions: Mix.
Spread over spinach mixture and top with mushroom buttons.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: sloppy joe hot dish
directions: In medium skillet, cook hamburger and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in catsup, mustard and soup. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatine in water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Heat soup; remove and add gelatine.
Cool.
Add cream cheese; beat with beater until smooth.
Cool.
Add salad dressing and lemon juice. Use mold ring.

title: lettuce and potato salad
directions: Slice romaine lettuce crosswise.
Pour in oil and vinegar and mix in tossing with lettuce.
Add salt, pepper, onion and diced potatoes.
Toss again and serve.

title: cola barbecue chicken
directions: Mix catsup and cola together.
Pour over chicken in iron skillet.
Bring to boil; turn down and let simmer for 30 minutes to an hour or until tender.

title: microwave frosted cauliflower
directions: Place cleaned and rinsed cauliflower in covered casserole. Microwave on High for 8 to 12 minutes.
Let stand for 3 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cauliflower.
Return and microwave for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: garlicky breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wrap garlic in aluminum foil and place in a small baking pan.
Bake in oven for 70 minutes or until soft. Remove from oven.
When cool enough to handle, unwrap garlic and cut off about 1/4-inch from top (not stem) of bulb.
With fingers, squeeze out soft garlic.
Puree in food processor with 1 tablespoon olive oil until smooth.

title: cranberry-jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello well in hot water. Stir in cranberries until broken up and mixed. Add crushed pineapple; stir well. Pour half of mixture (3 c.) into

serving container (8 x 12) dish. Place in refrigerator until completely jelled. Spread top of jelled mixture with sour cream. Pour remaining half of mixture (un-jelled-left out of refrigerator) over top of sour cream. Refrigerate until top layer is completely jelled.

title: bacon crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese, bacon, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and milk in small mixing bowl at medium speed.
Spread each crescent with 2 tablespoons of mixture.
To make more, cut each triangle in half diagonally.
Roll each triangle widest end first.
Once rolled, brush tops with melted butter and poppy seeds if you desire.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers in cold water; pack in jars with dill.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar to each jar.
Bring the water, vinegar and salt to boil; pour over cucumbers.
Seal.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 or 10-inch cast-iron baking sheet.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
In a small bowl combine butter, buttermilk and egg.
Add the liquids to the dry ingredients, pouring it into the well and stirring to form a soft dough.
Add raisins and mix lightly.
With lightly floured hands, shape into a ball on a baking sheet.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: topper corn bread
directions: Cook onion in butter just until tender, but not brown. Prepare the mix according to package directions.
Spread batter on greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over batter; dot onion-butter mixture over all.
Sprinkle with celery seed.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix all ingredients except meat and cheese.
Spread both sides of rolls generously.
Top with meat and slice of cheese.
Put top on . Put back on metal pan and cover with foil.
Heat at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 60.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chickens and save broth; take chicken off bones and chop into small pieces.
Saute onions, bell peppers and celery in margarine.
Add soups, chopped water chestnuts and chopped mushrooms.
Add grated Velveeta cheese.
Boil spaghetti in reserved chicken broth.
Drain spaghetti and combine with sauce and chicken.
Put into 2 casseroles.
If desired, slice olives and slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes nicely.

title: golden tomatoes
directions: Heat soup; add milk.
Toast bread and butter.
Place 3 or 4 tomato slices on each piece of toast.
Pour cheese sauce over tomatoes.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cherry cranberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine gelatin and sugar. Add water; stir until gelatin and sugar are dissolved. Stir in pineapple, cranberries, apples, celery and walnuts. Pour into a 2 quart serving bowl; chill until firm, about 3 to 4 hours.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Refrigerate for 2 days.
Slice in bite-size pieces.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Grease 3-quart casserole bowl.
Layer half of potatoes, half of hamburger meat, half of onion and half can of beans.
Start layers all over again, leaving potatoes on top.
Mix can of tomato soup with 1/2 can water.
Pour over all.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add water, lemon juice and rind. Cook over medium heat until thickens.
Remove from heat and add beaten egg yolks.
Stir until eggs are well blended.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 4 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Pour on top of pie.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mumpkin or monkey bread
directions: Make in Bundt cake pan.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Melt butter.
Add cinnamon and sugar and dissolve to make it sauce-like.
Pour over rolls and bake at 375° until brown; 30 to 40 minutes.
Dump on a plate.

title: blueberry snack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch square pan. Blend together, with mixer, first 9 ingredients on low speed 1 minute, then 2 1/2 minutes on high.
Combine 1 1/2 tablespoons flour, 1 tablespoon sugar and blueberries and gently fold into cake batter.
Spread in pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, cherries and nuts.
Melt butter and sugar; add dates and beaten egg.
Stir constantly and cook until thick (about 7 minutes).
Remove from heat and pour over Krispies mixture.
Shape into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: irish cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender 3 to 5 minutes on low. Put into a quart container and refrigerate. Shake well before serving.

title: manicotti
directions: Saute beef and garlic until browned.
Drain.
Mix together cottage cheese, Mozzarella, salt and mayonnaise.
Stir in beef. Cook manicotti in boiling water 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add cold water.
Remove manicotti from water, 1 at a time.
Fill with about 1/4 cup filling.
Place in single layer in 11 3/4 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle Parmesan cheese and oregano on top.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: agnes' fudge
directions: Boil the milk and sugar hard for 5 minutes.
Remove from the heat and add remaining ingredients; stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pan.
When cool, cut into pieces.
Can also use butterscotch or peanut butter chips instead of chocolate chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a buttered casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy as pie cake
directions: Pour pineapple and cherry pie filling in a large flat pan; mix.
Smooth dry cake mix over this evenly.
Melt butter to about room temperature and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli spears in bottom of casserole.
Mix together Cheez Whiz and soup and pour over broccoli.
Bake in oven at 400° until cheese is bubbly.
Sprinkle fried onions over top and bake for 4 to 5 minutes until brown and crunchy.

title: e-z barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients in saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: french applesauce cake
directions: Combine first eight ingredients in large bowl.
Heat applesauce in oil to warm and add to dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins, mix thoroughly.
Pour into tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Melt margarine and cream cheese.
Add corn and pimento.
Cook in heavy pot on low heat until hot and bubbly.

title: butterscotch toasties
directions: Melt butterscotch and peanut butter on top of stove, stirring constantly.
Add noodles and marshmallows.
Stir, coating ingredients.
Spoon onto wax paper and put in refrigerator for a couple of hours until they form.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen snacks, depending on size.

title: fresh tasting herb dip
directions: In food processor, combine all ingredients until smooth (about 30 seconds).
Cover and chill.
Serve with cut up vegetables.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soup, peas and carrots, seasonings and cheese, if desired.
Pour into a prepared pie crust.
Place top layer crust on top and cut several slits in the top of crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until crust is done.

title: bacon appetizers
directions: Cut whole water chestnuts into quarters.
Wrap with bacon strips and secure with a toothpick.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.
In a crock-pot add brown sugar, catsup, vinegar, steak sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add bacon wrapped chestnuts and simmer.
Serve warm.

title: coffee glazed ribs
directions: Arrange ribs one layer deep on bed of sauerkraut.
Heat and stir other ingredients until blended and pour over ribs.
Bake, uncovered, in 350°
oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Baste frequently. Makes 8 servings.

title: kielbasa appetizer
directions: Cut kielbasa into 2-3 inch pieces.
Place into crock pot. Pour pineapple topping over kielbasa.
Cook on high for 1 hour then turn to low for 2-3 hours.

title: fried bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, work in shortening.
Add water and mix well.
Shape into 6 balls of equal size.
Roll 1 ball at a time to 1/8-inch thickness; cut each into 6 wedges.
Fry in hot fat (375°) until puffy and brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: potatoes basque style
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Stir in parsley, pimento, pepper and broth.
Remove from heat.
Layer sliced potatoes in broth in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 20 minutes until potatoes are soft. Lift potatoes with slotted spoon onto heated serving dish.
Pour liquid over potatoes.

title: a-b-c soup
directions: In a large pot, combine broth, chicken, vegetables, celery, onion, thyme and bay leaf. Bring to boil; reduce heat and stir in macaroni.
Simmer for 12 to 15 minutes, or until vegetables and macaroni are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: korean fried beef strips
directions: Partially freeze beef, thinly slice across the grain into bite-size strips.
In a bowl, combine all measured ingredients. Soak meat for 30 minutes at room temperature.
Fry strips in oil until desired cooking time (how you prefer your meat cooked). Serve over cooked rice.

title: pork sausage ring
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Grease 6 1/2-cup mold.
Stuff sausage in mold and unmold onto jelly roll pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamiest chicken
directions: Roll breasts; place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine all other ingredients (reserve 1/2 cup of cheese) in one saucepan over low heat.
Stir until rich and creamy; pour sauce over chicken. Sprinkle reserved cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Place nuts and coconut in chopper and chop fine.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread pecans and coconut in pan and press. Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour over pecan mixture.
Mix cream cheese, oleo and sugar until very smooth and pours easily.
Pour over cake; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.
It will crack open.
Serve in squares with ice cream or Cool Whip, even plain.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core apples and chop into bite size pieces.
Add raisins and nuts (may also add seedless grapes, if desired).
Add mayonnaise to moisten, probably about 1 cup.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix 2 cups of chicken broth from the chicken with the soups. In baking pan, put layer of chicken, stuffing, then soup.
Repeat again.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated carrots(carrot salad)
directions: Heat tomato soup.
Do not boil.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Put carrots and diced vegetables into bowl.
Pour soup mixture over them.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli with not much water.
Add soup, milk, margarine, salt, pepper and tarragon.
Cook about 1/2 hour.
Add grated Velveeta.

title: golden onion rings
directions: Cut onions into slices 1/4 inch thick.
Separate into rings. Combine flour, salt, egg, milk and salad oil.
Beat together just until dry ingredients are well moistened.
Coat onion rings with batter.
Fry, a few at a time, in deep hot fat (375°), stirring once to separate rings.
When onions are golden, drain on paper towels.
Just before serving, sprinkle with salt.

title: sicilian broccoli
directions: Divide broccoli into flowerets and steam until cooked but still crisp.
Place in a warm serving dish.
In a small pan, melt butter.
Saute garlic in it for a few minutes and add sliced olives.
Pour butter mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and serve with lemon wedges.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Mix all together except chips.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips or fresh veggies.
Makes 2 cups.

title: broiled spanish mackerel(6 servings)
directions: Split fish.
Place on rack, skin side up, if skin has not been removed.
Broil at 450° until skin browns.
Turn.
Spread with butter; sprinkle with salt and paprika.
When brown, remove from pan.
Serve with lemon.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender. It doesn't matter what kind of juice you use. But it has to be frozen.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Puree 1 cup blackberries in blender. Strain and reserve juice. Reserve 6 tablespoons for cake and 6 tablespoons for icing.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except eggs. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well for 2 minutes on high speed.
Spoon batter into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tests done. Cool and frost.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients gradually; blend well.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with cake tester.
It should come out clean.

title: pear chips
directions: Grind oranges and lemons, using all except seeds.
Dissolve sugar in water.
Add all ingredients; cook until pears are clear and syrup thickens.
Seal in jars while hot.
Delicious on ice cream.
Yields 10 pints.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all.
Top with Ritz and butter before baking.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown
ground
beef,
bacon
and onion.
Drain off fat. Drain canned
beans.
Mix beans, browned meat mixture and all other ingredients in a casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup or gravy mix.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into serving slices and brown in skillet.
Place into baking dish.
Pour soup over mixture and bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: slaw without mayo
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard seed and water for 3 minutes; cool.
Chop cabbage, peppers and onions.
Pour vinegar mixture over cabbage; refrigerate. Will keep for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: brown edge honey wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a medium bowl, cream butter until smooth; then add sugar, honey and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy. Beat in egg white.
Stir in flour until combined.
Drop batter by 1/2 teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until edges are lightly browned.
Immediately transfer cookie to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
60 cookies, 25 calories each, 2 grams fat each.

title: black and white bean salad
directions: Rinse beans in cold water and drain.
Chop the onion.
Toss the beans, onion and parsley, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper together.
Serve at room temperature or chilled over romaine and/or variety of salad greens.
Salad may be made a day ahead.

title: fruit cocktail cake 1
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir in fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Frost while still warm.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg; beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Mix until blended.
Add lime juice and mix well.
Spoon into pie crust.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: potato cheddar casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery until almost done.
Mix all ingredients and bake in long baking dish at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, tomato sauce, water, seasonings and Parmesan cheese. Simmer for 30 minutes.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer noodles, meat sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cheeses are completely melted.

title: squash special
directions: Saute sausage and garlic until sausage is browned; drain. Cook squash in small amount of boiling water until tender; drain. Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Spoon into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: mom's pinto bean cake
directions: Grease and flour large tube pan or 2 loaf pans. Preheat oven to 350°. Cream together in large bowl the sugar, oil, egg and pinto beans until thoroughly blended. Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices. Add gradually to bean mixture, beating well each time. Fold in chopped apples, raisins and nuts. Pour into prepared pan or pans and bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: halloween pork chops
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Trim fat from chops.
Combine flour, garlic salt and dash of pepper.
Dip chops in mixture.
Brown chops well, about 10 to 15 minutes per side.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and cream cheese (which are at room temperature).
Add and beat in salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, until batter is smooth.
Stir in the flour and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Slowly add water and lemon juice and bring to a boil with 1 cup blueberries.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Pour hot mixture over remaining 3 cups berries (uncooked).
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: kristina's favorite vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients with hand mixer.
Serve with bite-size pieces of fresh vegetables.
Remember, no double dipping!!! Enough for party platter.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip. Blend.
Pour into crust and chill until firm.

title: italian spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper and celery until beef is brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems, chop and set aside.
Brush outside of caps with some of the butter; place caps in a buttered shallow 9-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining butter, onion and chopped stems in a saucepan; saute 5 minutes.
Stir in breadcrumbs, walnuts, salt and pepper.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Have tomatoes washed and sliced. You may or may not peel.
Put layer of tomatoes in unbaked shell, then sprinkle a layer of dry ingredients.
Repeat and sprinkle 1 tablespoon of vinegar and a small amount of butter over the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "mock" sour cream raisin pie
directions: For first bite, dip large, washed strawberry (preferably with stem on) in sour cream then into brown sugar.
Like it?
Repeat.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks; mash yolks with fork.
Mix with salt, mustard, pepper and mayonnaise. Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping lightly.
Sprinkle yolks with paprika.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except lemon pepper.
Form into one or two balls.
Roll in lemon pepper.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least overnight.
Allow to stand approximately 1 hour uncovered before serving.

title: french-fried potato salad
directions: Pour the water into large saucepan.
Bring to full, rolling boil.
Carefully drop frozen potatoes into water.
Remove from heat immediately; cover and let stand 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain potatoes at once.
Spread on paper toweling.
Cut up any large pieces.
Sprinkle potatoes with the salt; cool.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix all ingredients into a 1 1/2 quart bowl.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: blueberry icebox pie
directions: Bake graham cracker crusts at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Place softened cream cheese, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla in a mixing bowl and mix together with beater.
Pour mixture together into the cooled baked pie crust.
Add blueberry mix on top and spread evenly.
Chill.
Tastes best if chilled overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add soups (undiluted); stir in meat and 1/2 stick of margarine (melted) and bread cubes.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix potato chips and 1/2 stick of margarine (melted) and sprinkle over the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set up.

title: low-fat chili pie
directions: The size baking dish or pan depends on how much you want to make.
Spray with Pam or other baking spray.
Crush chips in bottom, then layer chili or beans, cheese and more chips.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake in 300° oven for about 40 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Toss all the ingredients together except the Fritos, adding chilled Catalina dressing.
Add Fritos just before serving.

title: fat-free mocha fudge cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, combine prune butter, coffee and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add mixture to flour mixture.
Mix well. Add walnuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with nonstick cooking spray; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Sift confectioners sugar over cool cake.

title: red berry mold
directions: Prepare gelatin according to directions.
Pour half into 1 1/2-quart dish.
Chill until thickened like egg white.
Stir in berries (thawed).
Return to fridge.
Also, chill remaining gelatin.

title: sweet gherkins
directions: First Day:
Wash cucumbers thoroughly and drain.
Place in large container and cover with boiling water.
Six to 8 hours later, drain and cover with fresh boiling water.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix crab, mayonnaise and horseradish. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Microwave for 3 to 5 minutes, or until bubbles appear on the edges.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon; break in small pieces.
Brown hamburger with onions.
Mix in beans and rest of ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot for 1 1/2 hours.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Stir together sugar, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Mix with pickle mixture and stir several times for 4 or 5 days, while keeping in refrigerator.
Then put into containers and freeze.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix half the cheese with baking mix and sausage.
Stuff peppers with remaining cheese.
Pinch together lightly.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick. Wrap each jalapeno in dough.
Remove excess dough and seal completely.
Shape each like an egg.
Roll each one in seasoned mix, dip in beaten egg and roll in seasoned mix again. Arrange on a baking sheet and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken, chuck and ham together in a large heavy covered stockpot with enough water to cover until the chicken is tender (approximately 40 minutes).
Add more water if necessary.
Remove the chicken from the pot to allow to cool until you can handle, then remove the bones and cut the meat into small pieces.
Return the meat to the pot.
Add the Great Northerns, cubed potatoes, onions, pepper flakes, ketchup, canned tomatoes, tomato paste, soup, Worcestershire, Tabasco, salt, pepper and butter.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add frozen vegetables; cover and cook for 1 more hour, stirring occasionally.

title: rice and beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain fat. Combine beef with uncooked rice, mushroom soup, carrots, onion, celery, water and soy sauce. Place in a large well-greased casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Stir once when casserole is half done.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, punch holes in hot cake and pour syrup over it.
Cool in refrigerator.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Put on top, then top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash, boil, drain, cool, peel and slice or cube potatoes. Hard-cook eggs, cool, peel and cut in half.
Dice whites, reserve yolks for dressing.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add well-beaten eggs. Sift flour, salt and cocoa three times; add dry ingredients, alternate with buttermilk. Add vanilla. Blend food coloring. Dissolve soda in vinegar and fold into batter. Bake in three layers in a 350° oven.

title: stewed crabs
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil. Drop crabs into boiling water with grease from fried-out white bacon. Cook until meat is white and crabs turn red. Mix cornmeal and water until smooth. Add to crabs and cook until thick. Sprinkle pepper over top. Serve hot.

title: tomato-feta frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat greased oven-safe skillet in oven for about 5 minutes.
Beat eggs with water.
Add rice, cheeses, picante sauce, cilantro and oregano.
Pour mixture into prepared skillet.
Top with tomatoes.
Bake for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugar free cheesecake
directions: Mix gelatine and sugar in small bowl. Add boiling water and stir until gelatine dissolves completely, about 5 minutes. Place walnuts in pan, place in oven at 300° for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool nuts, then process

in food processor until well ground. Pat them in the bottom of a 9 inch pie pan. Beat cream cheese and vanilla in large bowl with mixer until smooth. Add instant mocoa coffee and blend well. Slowly beat in gelatine mixture. Pour into prepared crust.
Refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; mix well. Add liquid ingredients. Beat or mix until smooth. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes or until firm.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Fill canning jars with peeled sliced apples.
Cover apples with this syrup. Pressure 5 pounds for 8 minutes.

title: "weight on" food for dogs
directions: Mix together.
To serve, mix 1 cup dry dog food with 1 large handful of hamburger.
Should have observable results in 2 weeks.

title: italian relish
directions: Chop all veggies fine.
Combine with oil and vinegar. Marinate for several hours.

title: smoothy
directions: Put all into a blender on high speed until smooth.
You may add protein powder.

title: steak marinade
directions: Pour over raw meat and let soak several hours.
Turn meat every hour or two.
May be left overnight in refrigerator until time to cook meat.

title: roast pork
directions: Take a piece of pork and have it split or boned.
Place a piece of linguica in the center of the pork and roll up and tie securely.
Roast in a 350° oven until tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours, add potatoes, cut up, if desired).

title: cling peach upside-down cake
directions: Drain peaches.
Line 9-inch cake pan with heavy-duty Reynolds wrap.
Let foil extend about 2-inches above rim.
Melt butter in pan.
Sprinkle sugar and almonds over butter.
Arrange peaches and cherries over sugar.
Mix cake batter according to package directions.
Pour over peaches.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Invert pan on cake plate; remove pan and peel off foil.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Grate potatoes last because they will turn brown if they are not cooked soon after grating.
Roll meatballs in bread crumbs.
They will be soft; if they are too soft add more bread crumbs.
Fry meatballs in 1/2-inch of oil, turning frequently.
Place in serving dish and cover with any mushroom sauce.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: texas tacos
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add taco mix, tomato sauce and 1 1/2 cans water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon over Fritos.
Top with toppings and serve.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 1/2 x 12-inch pan.
Combine flour, milk and sugar in a bowl.
Pour flour mixture in pan with oleo.
Pour peaches on top of flour-oleo mixture.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Any kind of fruit can be used.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in ice cream freezer.

title: bean burritos
directions: Combine first two ingredients.
Set aside.
Spoon heaping 1 cup of bean mixture and ladle of cheese onto center of each tortilla.
Roll up tortillas to enclose filling.
Place, seam side down, in an 11 x 7-inch microwave dish.
Pour taco sauce evenly over burritos.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Loosely cover dish.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce and tomato on top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and beat together the eggs, oil and sugar. Add and sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Add apples, nuts and vanilla. Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cut beans in small pieces; toss with lemon juice and steam until tender.
Combine tomatoes, onion, carrots, celery and pepper in stockpot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer one to two hours or until vegetables are tender.
Add beans and cabbage. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add chicken and rice or pasta.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: cranberry coffee bars
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients, then add flour, baking powder and beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts and add cranberry sauce.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
While warm, frost with lemon butter frosting. (Confectioners sugar, warm milk, butter and lemon juice.)
Cut in small squares.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well with remaining ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: dilled corn and pea pods
directions: In medium saucepan, combine frozen corn and water.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 4 minutes.
Cut pepper into bite-size strips.
Add red pepper and pea pods to saucepan.
Cover and cook about 2 minutes or until red pepper and pea pods are crisp-tender; drain.
Add margarine, dill weed, salt and pepper to vegetable mixture.
Stir until margarine melts and vegetables are coated.
Serves 5.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil the squash until tender. Drain liquid and mash. Saute the onion, bell pepper and water chestnuts in the oleo.
Fold in the cheese, mayonnaise, sugar, egg and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian cookies
directions: Beat eggs well and add remaining ingredients.
Dough will be sticky.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost with thin powdered sugar frosting while still warm.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Refrigerate 12 hours before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until set.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine everything and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour hot sauce over 4 pounds of meat and bake 2 or 3 hours at 250°.

title: 100% bran low-fat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar in another bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and applesauce; add to flour mixture. Stir just until moistened.
May be lumpy.
Spoon batter into muffin tins (2/3 full) which have been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until brown.
Makes 12.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy.
Serve with apple slices (leave the skin on).

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the first four ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and spread on top.
Add cheese to top and refrigerate.

title: 100% parmesan bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix cheese, margarine and Italian seasoning; spread on bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Heat milk
with
sugar, butter and salt until butter is melted, then cool.	Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Beat egg. When milk is
cooled add yeast and egg mixture and pour all at once into flour.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Cover tightly and store
in refrigerator overnight or for 1/2 day.
Top with your own sauce and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins or use cupcake papers.
Cream sweet potatoes, butter, sugar, egg and salt.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add alternately with milk and mix well.
Add chopped pecans and raisins, if desired.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes, depending on your oven.
(A toothpick inserted in the middle will tell you if they're done.)

title: clam dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glogg(swedish glogg)
directions: Combine wine, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, cardamon and orange peel in saucepan. Stir to blend.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Heat, but do not boil.
Light with a match and pour burning into heatproof cups containing a few almonds and raisins.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine salmon, oats, onion, egg, parsley, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into 4 patties.
Pan-fry on both sides in hot oil until golden brown.
Serve in buns with lettuce and tomatoes.
Serves 4.

title: mallow topped sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together, except marshmallows in 1 quart casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows. Bake 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheddar cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter together; add remaining ingredients. Mix well
with
mixer or processor until mixture cleans sides of bowl and
forms
a ball.
Stir in 1 cup chopped nuts. Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill;
cut into squares. Makes about 6 pounds.

title: carrot bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan.
Assemble blender. Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Blend chopped nuts.
Add to dry ingredients. Put eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla extract into container, cover and process at mix until smooth.
Stop blender, add carrot pieces, cover and process at liquefy.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes in pan, then turn out on cake rack and cool.

title: old fashioned blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Reserve 1 tablespoon to toss with berries.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Combine milk, eggs and butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Toss berries with reserved flour mix.
Stir into batter.
Spoon into greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: cherry angel squares
directions: Break angel food cake into chunks and place half in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over cake; top with remaining cake chunks.
Mix pudding with milk as directed on package.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour over cherry cake mixture and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Mix well.
Place on floured surface.
You may have to add flour until dough is not sticky and can be rolled thin.
Let dry at least 1 hour; roll and cut.

title: helen thompson's cantaloupe pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in heavy saucepan.
Coarsely grind and drain cantaloupe using food processor.
Do not use blender.
Add eggs, butter and cantaloupe to sugar-flour mixture and cook over low heat until very thick, stirring constantly.
Watch closely to prevent scorching.
Pour thick mixture into pie shell and cool in refrigerator.

title: glazed grapefruit
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over halved grapefruit.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Check occasionally.
Garnish with a strawberry.

title: teriyaki
directions: For marinade, combine soy sauce, salad oil, molasses, ginger, dry mustard and minced garlic cloves; mix well.
If marinade is to be used on steak, score meat on both sides.
Marinate overnight and let stand 15 minutes at room temperature before cooking on grill.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours until it gets real cold.
If you prefer a different color, put cake coloring in. It doesn't change the flavor.

title: corn pudding
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Cool, so it won't cook eggs.
Add sugar, salt, flour, milk, cheese and corn.
Stir in eggs.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish in a preheated 350° oven.

title: clifford tea cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, salt and soda and add with the nuts.
Pack in mold and leave overnight in refrigerator and slice as thin as possible.
Cook until light brown in a 350° oven.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients;
blend in the Osterizer.

title: fork-tender spareribs(microwave)
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, place spareribs, bone side up.
Add water. Cover tightly with plastic wrap, leaving one corner open for vent.
Microwave on Medium for 40 minutes.
Turn ribs over and arrange onion and lemon over top. Return to microwave for an additional 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Drain liquid from ribs and pour on sauce.
Microwave on Medium for 10 to 15 minutes, loosely covered with plastic wrap, until sauce has dried on top. Spoon sauce over ribs before serving.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine butter, graham crackers and sugar.
Mix well.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: soft caraway cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg and applesauce.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to butter-sugar mixture with caraway seed and vanilla.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
While cookies are still warm, frost with a glaze made with the juice of half a lemon, the grated rind and enough powdered sugar to make it spread easily.

title: celery clam soup
directions: Pour soup, milk, clam juice and thyme in saucepan.
Stir over low flame until smooth.
Cover; chill.
Cut scraped carrot into sticks and cook in boiling salted water.
Drain; chill.
Mix carrot into soup just before serving cold.

title: cheese strata with zucchini
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter baking dish.
Cut onion and zucchini into thin slices.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in frying pan; add onion and zucchini.
Simmer until soft and brown.
Add marjoram and oregano.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Grate cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Layer bread, vegetables and cheese in baking dish and pour milk mixture over all.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake 30 minutes until browned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix peaches and lemon juice.
Stir together sugar, flour and cinnamon; mix with peaches. Pour into pastry-lined pie pan; dot with butter.

Cover with top crust which has slits cut in it; seal and flute around edges. Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning; remove foil the last 15 minutes of baking. Bake pie for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in bowl. Mix cereal, milk and sugar; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir egg whites into applesauce.
Add to flour; stir just until moist.
Spoon into muffin pan sprayed with no stick cooking spray.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together with the bacon.
Mix all into the dressing.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco until fluffy.
Add sugars and eggs. Add milk and flour, mixed with salt and baking powder, alternately.
Add vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Turn into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 25 minutes before removing from pan.
This is baked in a tube pan.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream butter and eggs.
Add sugar and syrup.
Mix well.
Work in nuts and a pinch of salt.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: lynn's pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle (dry) cake mix on top.
Melt butter and pour over this. Add chopped pecans to top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in 1/2 cup buttermilk and wait to add later.
Add remaining milk alternately with flour then add soda mixture, chocolate, vanilla and salt.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips over boiling water.
Stir in milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal, peanuts and raisins.
Mix until thoroughly coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.
Makes about 2 pounds or 48 pieces.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine cake flour and baking soda.
Set aside.
In another bowl blend sugar, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla, vinegar and food coloring.
Slowly stir in cake flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (makes 3 layers).
Don't forget to grease and flour three 8-inch cake pans.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix according to package directions.
Thaw broccoli and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add next 3 ingredients; stir until smooth.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely; spread with Chocolate Frosting.

title: turkey-salad souffle
directions: Cube 2 slices of the bread; place in the bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine turkey, vegetables, mayonnaise and seasoning; spoon over bread cubes.
Trim crusts from remaining bread; arrange slices over turkey mixture.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over all.
Cover and chill 1 hour or overnight.
Spoon soup over top and bake in a 325° oven for about 1 hour or until set.
Sprinkle cheese over top last few minutes of baking.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Wilt large cabbage leaves in hot water. Roll small amount of mixture in each leaf and fasten with a toothpick.
Pour enough boiling water over rolls to cover.
Boil until tender.
Add 1 quart tomatoes.
Heat well before serving.

title: broiled baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Rub skin side of breasts with butter. Season with salt, lemon pepper and paprika.
Place breasts in shallow pan, skin side up.
Cook in oven under broiler until nice and brown.
Turn oven to 325°.
Cook chicken breasts about 3/4 hour or until tender when pricked with a fork.

title: refrigerated cabbage slaw
directions: Shred or slice cabbage (thin); chop up onion and green pepper. Add vinegar and sugar.
Stir well and place in refrigerator overnight.
Chop up tomato and add and stir.
Taste to see if you need to add salt.
Add a dash or two of coarse black pepper.
I also add 2 teaspoons mustard seed.
It gives it a great taste. Put slaw in a container that will seal.
Turn upside down in refrigerator.
Pour off liquid before serving.
If needed add more sugar and vinegar.

title: virgin mary(nonalcoholic mixed drink)
directions: Combine liquid ingredients and seasonings in a mixing glass. Shake with ice and strain into a highball or Collins glass filled with ice cubes.
Garnish with celery stalk and wedge of lime. Makes 1 serving.
Preparation time: 5 minutes.

title: kids' pudding pies(cool refreshing snack for summer)
directions: Blend peanut butter with milk until smooth.
Add pudding mix and blend for 2 minutes.
Chill this mixture for 5 minutes. Spread about 1/2-inch thick between graham crackers.
Freeze at least 2 hours.
This makes about 20 snacks.

title: easy crowd cake
directions: Mix cake as package directs.
Bake in prepared jelly roll pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, milk and instant pudding mix.
Spread on cooled cake.
Sprinkle with drained pineapple.
Blend Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Spread over pineapple layer.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds or chopped nuts.

title: russian rocks
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour and other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 or 7 dozen cookies.

title: sausage roll
directions: Brown sausage and onion until done.
Beat egg and milk together.
Make pizza dough as directed on package.
Flatten dough and brush 3/4 of the egg and milk over it.
Spread sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Roll dough and sausage into a roll.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: frosting
directions: Melt butter, cocoa and milk.
Add powdered sugar.
Heat and pour over cake.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
In large bowl, combine melted chocolate mixture, 1 cup of the flour, granulated sugar, eggs, baking powder and salt.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining 1 cup flour and the nuts.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Place butter in a 9 x 13 baking dish and put in oven until it melts. In a medium bowl combine flour, milk and sugar. Mix well. Pour mixture into baking dish. Add peaches on top and bake for 25 to 30 minutes

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cook turnips and carrots for 10 minutes in boiling water with 1/2 teaspoon salt added.
Add peas and cook until tender, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain; season with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: cherry cool whip freeze
directions: Mix in order given.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: lemonade pies
directions: Mix lemonade, milk and Cool Whip together.
Pour in crusts and let set in refrigerator before serving.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Mix sausage and cheese together until thoroughly blended.
On lightly floured surface, roll each pastry rectangle until it's about 8 inches by 14 inches.
Divide sausage mixture in half and form each into tube shape, about 13 inches long.
Lay each sausage roll along one long edge of pastry rectangle and roll up, jelly roll fashion, to form two long logs.
(Recipe may be made to this point up to 24 hours before serving.
Cover sausage roll with plastic wrap until ready to finish and serve.)

title: freezer tomato sauce
directions: Place tomatoes in large kettle with onions, carrots, parsley, sugar, salt and pepper.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in casserole.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Put first seven ingredients together, mixing thoroughly with electric mixer.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
When cake is cool, either frost with icing or drizzle with glaze.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine candies and cider.
Heat slowly, stirring, until candies have dissolved.
Hold at a simmer to serve.
A party percolator or stoneware slow cooker works well for both heating and serving.

title: indians
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa and blend well.
Add sugar and then eggs (unbeaten), one at a time, beating each one well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and cut in squares.
Let cool before removing from the 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: tuna mushroom a la king
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Blend in soup.
Gradually stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat and stir. Serve over toast.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix flour, 1/2 cup chopped nuts, 1 stick butter and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Spread on bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° and let cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and add dressing.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Place all dry ingredients into a large bowl; add shortening and vanilla; mix as you would a pie crust. Break eggs into a 1 cup measure and fill with milk. Add liquid to mixture, mixing well. Chill, roll, and cut into shapes. Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Can also be dropped.

title: ruth's fruit salad
directions: Use 2 cups of juice from the cans of fruit and mix with the vanilla pudding.
Bring to a boil.
Stir.
Let it cool.
Before serving, pour over fruit.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Crush 1/2 box cheese crackers over top of casserole. Slowly pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: percolator punch, ii
directions: Mix brown sugar and spices in basket of percolator, juices and water in bottom.
Allow to perk 10 to 12 minutes.

title: party turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine meat and onion soup mix.
Brown in medium skillet.
Blend in cheese. Separate crescent dough according to directions.
Then cut each triangle in half.
Place teaspoon of mixture in center of each triangle.
Fold over and seal edges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 48.

title: finger licking hungarian ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine paprika, salt and pepper.
Rub seasonings evenly over ribs.
Place ribs in single layer in shallow baking pan and top with sliced onions. Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender in 2-quart pan or bigger. Add remaining ingredients. Stir over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.
Other veggies can be added, if desired.

title: delmonico nut cake
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, cream butter or margarine and shortening thoroughly.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Sift flour with soda three times, then add to batter alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry mixture.
By hand stir in coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Stir in heaping tablespoon into batter and beat by hand vigorously until blended, then carefully fold in remaining egg whites.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° (or 350° for metal), 1 hour or until cake tests done or bake in greased, floured 8-inch pans at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate buttercream frosting
directions: In large bowl, beat together sugar, butter, vanilla, chocolate and milk until smooth.
If necessary, add more milk until frosting is spreading consistency.
Stir to blend.
Makes enough to fill and frost 2-layer cake or 13 x 9-inch sheet cake or 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: hamburger-potato-carrot casserole
directions: Combine all of ingredients and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Beat well.
Beat until smooth. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 deep 8 or 9-inch layer pans lined with paper.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: low calorie fruit dessert
directions: Spray bottom of casserole dish with Pam.
Pour fruit into dish; sprinkle lemon juice on top of fruit.
Spread dry cake mix over fruit.
Melt margarine; spread over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: mexicali chicken
directions: Cook chicken in oil over medium heat about 15 minutes or until brown.
Drain off fat.
Mix sauce for tacos:
water, salt, oregano, instant garlic and instant onion.
Pour over chicken.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: mystery barley soup
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, cook oxtail pieces over medium heat until lightly browned.

Add onions and cook until tender. Add water, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 4 hours to blend flavors and reduce volume by half. Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer until barley is cooked, about 45 minutes.
Skim off excess fat before serving.

title: citrus and onion salad
directions: In small jar with tight fitting lid, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, seasoned salt and mustard; shake to blend well.
In shallow dish, layer oranges, grapefruit and onion; pour the dressing over to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Remove fruit slices and onion from marinade; reserve marinade.
Arrange on individual salad plates lined with the spinach leaves.

title: paprika vegetable and sausage stew
directions: In a medium sized flameproof casserole, heat the oil to moderate heat.
When the oil is hot, add the onion and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 7 minutes or until onions are soft and translucent but not brown.

Add the green and red peppers and cook, stirring occasionally, for another 5 minutes. Remove the casserole from the heat and stir in the paprika, salt, pepper, dill and the tomatoes without the juice, mixing well to blend.
Return the casserole to low heat and simmer the mixture for 25 to 30 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Stir in the potatoes, sausage and sour cream and simmer over low heat for a further 5 minutes or until the potatoes and sausage are heated through.
Remove the casserole from the heat and serve at once.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars (white and brown) until fluffy. Add egg; blend in salad oil.
Add oatmeal, cornflakes, coconut and nuts.
Stir well.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Form into balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water or use bottom of a small glass dipped in water.
Bake at 325° for about 12 minutes.
Flatten cookies as much as you can for a crisper cookie.
Good without nuts and coconut.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in bacon drippings.
Cook limas and drain.
Add to onion.
Add remaining ingredients, including 1/2 the cheese.
Heat, then turn into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remainder of cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tanya's famous pb&j
directions: Take a generous scoop of peanut butter and place on one slice of bread.
Take an equal scoop of jelly.
Smooth on other slice of bread.
Combine 2 slices of bread.
Enjoy!

title: pineapple cobbler
directions: Mix together the crushed pineapple, juice and all, sugar, cornstarch, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Cook on top of double boiler until thick.
(I cook mine in the microwave) Cool.
Set aside.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick of butter, 1 egg and nuts.
Pack in bottom of a greased sheet cake pan.
Mix 3 eggs, cream cheese, box of powdered sugar and vanilla lemon extract.
Beat until smooth. Pour on top of packed cake mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Done when top is golden brown.)

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Mix garlic salt, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix in the rest of ingredients and stir and shake several times during cooking.
Cook at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: heavenly onion casserole
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over low heat.
Saute onions and mushrooms until tender.
Put this in 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Combine soup, milk and soy sauce.
Pour this over cheese mixture.
Top with bread and cheese slices.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
Bake in 375° oven, loosely covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pea casserole
directions: Boil peas until almost cooled.
Drain; add celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Season to taste.
Mix stuffing with butter.
Sprinkle on peas.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter and when cool, add lemon juice and set aside.
Mix all seafood together carefully.
Add butter/lemon mixture and mix again.
Place in a shallow baking dish, such as Pyrex or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add about 1/4 to 1/2 cup water and sprinkle a little paprika on top.
Cut the remaining 1/2 stick of butter into small pieces on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes, stirring periodically in a basting fashion, so you can keep the meat in large pieces.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Combine dates, water and raisins; boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream together eggs, sweetener, margarine, vanilla, banana, apple butter and applesauce.
Sift together flour, spices and soda.
Combine three mixtures together.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Combine butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in large saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: aunt stella's cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in 2 cups water with a dash of salt.
Into hot grits, melt the margarine and cheese.
Add salt and milk.
Bake at 350° in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.
It will puff up like a souffle.

title: poor man's stew
directions: Fry hamburger with diced onion.
Boil potatoes and mash as usual.
Place hamburger in bottom of medium casserole dish.
Pour creamed corn evenly over hamburger (other vegetables may be added, if desired).
Place mashed potatoes on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Have salad and biscuits for a complete meal.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Cut lemons in thin slices.
Place in a bowl and cover with sugar.
Mash thoroughly until all juice is extracted.
Add water. Let stand 1 hour.
Strain.
Allow 1 or 2 tablespoons of the strained lemon juice for each serving.
Pour into glass filled with shaved ice and add water.
Garnish with maraschino cherry and slice of lemon.
Yields 3 or 4 servings.

title: baked stew
directions: Cut vegetables in serving pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a roasting pan.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until done.
Can be baked at 250° for 3 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour, beaten eggs to buttermilk then add to other ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 425° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce to 325° and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until firm (may want to add 1 cup of coconut to mixture for different taste).

title: chicken with stuffing
directions: Lay chicken breasts in baking dish.
Put 1 slice of cheese on top of each one.
Spread soup over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle croutons over top.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.
Simple, but very good! Easy to adapt for more or less servings.

title: fudge ice cream pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Put Pet milk, chips and salt in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts completely and mixture is thick.
Take off heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until mix is smooth.
Cool to room temperature.

title: sausage and pasta casserole
directions: Prepare ziti as directed.
Drain.
Add 3/4 cup margarine. Mix; set aside.
In large skillet cook sausage until no pink remains.
Remove from skillet.
Drain fat.
Cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Combine in casserole dish with the pasta, sausage, onion, garlic, spaghetti, half the Mozzarella cheese, all the basil, oregano and pepper.
Mix together. Sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: molasses shake
directions: Combine ingredients in shaker or blend until frothy.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Combine soups, pimento and cheese.
Add soup mixture and chicken to spaghetti and broth; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and brown.
Place on paper towel to drain. Beat eggs, salt, pepper and evaporated milk together.
Cook grits according to package directions.
Leave thinner than normal. Layer grits, sausage, onions, cheese and eggs in casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until eggs are set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Drain chicken, chunk into bite-size pieces.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Grill or broil chicken; slice crosswise.
Combine with vegetables in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour over salad; mix gently.
Chill, stirring occasionally, for about 3 hours.
Serve on lettuce lined platter.
Serves 4.

title: cherry chocolate crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in 2-quart glass dish.
Melt margarine. Add to dry cake mix, nuts and coconut.
Mix well with fork. Place on top of pie filling and microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes. Sprinkle top with coconut.

title: portia's spanish rice(one dish meal-spanish rice)
directions: Steam the rice in 2 cups water.
Brown the ground beef; drain off the juice.
Add the chopped onion and cook over low heat until clear.
Add the tomato soup, the El Pato sauce and the cooked rice. Salt to taste.
Simmer on low for 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim all the fat off the round steak.
Cut in squares; put in paper bag with flour.
Shake to coat well.
Brown beef in pan with 1/2 to 1 stick margarine.
Work with spatula until well browned. Salt and pepper meat.
Add the consomme or bouillon and the water. Cover tightly in slow cooker; simmer until tender (bubbly boil about 1 hour).

title: pepperoni pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper in saucepan; break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir macaroni and pepperoni into mixture.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes until hot and cheese is brown in 350° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kentucky stack cake
directions: Cream sorghum, butter and sugar until well blended. Mix milk with well-beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture alternately with egg-milk liquid. Stir until smooth only. Divide batter into 6 equal amounts of 1 cup batter in each. Spread batter in well-greased 9-inch cake pans. Makes 6 layers. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove layers from pans and stack layers with applesauce on each layer. Sweeten and/or spice applesauce to taste.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook ground meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain on paper towel.
Return to skillet; add remaining ingredients and simmer 40 to 45 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Makes 6 servings.
One-thousand calorie recipe.

title: italian spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown meat, onion and cloves of garlic.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, water, salt, pepper, red pepper, sugar and mushrooms. Mix well.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti with garlic French bread.

title: killer cornbread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat egg in a large bowl.
Stir in buttermilk, molasses and butter.
Stir in flour mixture.
Mix in walnuts and raisins.
Scrape batter into prepared pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes or until well browned.
Remove from oven and place pan on wire rack to cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Drain and wash peas. Mix with onions and green pepper. Mix in remaining ingredients. Let stand, covered, in the refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain green, wax and garbanzo beans. Drain and rinse the kidney beans.
Mix all beans, green pepper and onions.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves. Pour over bean mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring several times.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, shortening, coconut and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and oats.
Form into balls; press with a fork. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt oleo in skillet with 1/2 cup sugar. While it cooks, in another pan, cook 2 cups sugar and milk. Add sugar mixture when it is brown. Cook like fudge until it forms soft balls in cold water. Will ice 2 layers for cake.

title: creamed soup mix
directions: Combine the ingredients; mix and store in an airtight container.
The recipe makes 3 cups of mix which, when reconstituted, will produce the equivalent of nine 10 ounce cans of soup.
When you are ready to use, combine 1/3 cup of the mix with 1 1/4 cups of water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened. If you want to use this in place of cream of celery soup, add 1/4 cup chopped celery.
For mushroom soup, add 1/4 cup chopped, fresh or canned mushrooms or 1 tablespoon of dried mushrooms.
Serving size:
1/3 cup of mix is equal to one 10 ounce can of soup.

title: scripture cake
directions: Check Bible for all ingredients.
Follow instructions of basic cake recipe.
Bake in very low oven at 275° for 3 to 4 hours. Enjoy.

title: hot pork dish
directions: In a skillet, heat oil; cook pork, celery, red/green pepper and onion until the meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
In a large bowl, combine pork mixture, noodles, soups, corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Turn into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: hummus(greek appetizer)
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor with steel knife attachment.
Process until smooth.
Taste for seasoning.
