Spoon into bowl.
Serve with "Akmak" crackers.

title: linguini and white clam sauce
directions: Melt butter and oil; add onion and saute.
Add garlic and cook for 2 more minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except linguini and flour/water.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix flour in water.
Add to simmering clam sauce to thicken.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, remove from bone and cut up.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream together.
Add to chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers and spread on top.
Melt butter and pour over crackers. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: easy broccoli rice casserole
directions: You will need a large casserole dish, lightly greased, and aluminum foil.

title: peppermint bark
directions: Break bark into pieces and place in 3-quart bowl.
Microwave at 50% power for approximately 5 to 6 minutes, until pieces are soft. Stir after 3 minutes.
While bark is melting, process candy in food processor until it is a fine powder.
Add candy to melted bark and stir well.
Spread on wax paper 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick.
Cool in refrigerator until hard.
Break into pieces.
Freezes well.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread hamburger over the bottom of baking dish.
Spread dry onion soup mix over meat.
Add green beans.
Spread soups over vegetables.
Spread Tater Tots over the top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 400 degrees.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: christmas hardtack
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to 278°.
Add flavoring (1/4 teaspoon) and coloring (1/4 teaspoon).
Pour immediately onto a buttered marble (or other smooth, heat absorbing marble surface). Use a knife and cut into 3/4-inch lengths, then snip into bite size pieces with kitchen scissors.
Butter hands to work with candy.

title: heavenly chocolate ice cream
directions: Cut candy into pieces.
Combine with sweetened condensed milk (Eagle Brand).
Cook over low heat in a saucepan, stirring constantly, until candy is melted.
Cool.
Add 1 quart of milk. Beat well.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Stir in chocolate syrup.
Add remaining milk and freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: boiled salad dressing
directions: Put the butter, flour, sugar, eggs, mustard, salt and pepper into a bowl or the inner part of a double boiler and cook over hot water till they begin to thicken.
Add the vinegar and continue the cooking three minutes.
Beat the mixture occasionally while cooling.
Keep in refrigerator.
This dressing will remain good several weeks.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop squash in 1-inch pieces (or less).
In large skillet, melt oleo and saute onion and squash.
Beat eggs.
Chop cheese into small cubes (1/2-inch).
Place squash and onion in casserole dish; mix in egg and cheese cubes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until brown on top.

title: shirley's cheese cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
moderate
Combine
cake
mix, butter and 1 of the eggs in a large bowl;
mix well.
Pat down into an even layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture (use white sugar and cinnamon and make mixture).
Put 1/2 of the biscuits in a greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans and/or raisins over biscuits.
Melt butter and add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half of this over biscuits.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: san antonio cream peas
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add chilies and dried mint and cook a minute or so to heat through.
Add cream and salt to taste and let it almost come to a boil.
Remove from heat, place in a blender or food processor, whirl smooth and put back in the pan.
Bring to a boil over high heat and cook down, stirring until reduced and slightly thickened.
Put peas in boiling salted water and cook only until the water comes to a boil again. Drain them and put in the cream sauce.
Cover and simmer 1 to 2 minutes. Serves 4.

title: frozen chocolate chip pie
directions: Sift sugar, salt and cream of tartar together.
Beat whites stiff, adding dry ingredients gradually while beating.
Fold in vanilla and chopped pecans and place in greased pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Let cool.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix ingredients.
Spread mixture evenly in pan.
Lightly sprinkle top with Parmesan and paprika.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into pieces about 2 x 1-inch.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and lemon juice. Chill jello and stir in the remaining ingredients.

title: green chili cheese grits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Freezes well before baking.

title: carolyn's taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix together.
Add peppers.
Spread on plate.
Add lettuce, olives,
and cut up tomatoes.
Top with shredded cheese.
Serve with nachos.

title: yamazetti
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Brown meat with half the onion and 2 tablespoons green pepper.
Add tomato soup, water and mushrooms. Add remaining ingredients (including remaining raw onion) to drained noodles.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chile cornbread
directions: Saute peppers, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Stir in pepper, hot sauce and corn; cook until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat; cool.
Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine 2 cups flour and next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Gradually stir into yeast mixture.

Add eggs, one at a time, mixing with hands until smooth. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface; knead in softened butter, 1 tablespoon at a time, until dough is smooth and elastic. Place dough in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries.
Mix pineapple, bananas and nuts together.
Add to gelatin.
Pour half of mixture into a 13 x 8-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream on chilled gelatin.
Gently pour remaining mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate until congealed and ready to serve.

title: crusty potato pancakes(servings:  6.  preparation time:  45 minutes.)
directions: Grate potatoes into a bowl filled with cold water.
In another bowl, combine onion, eggs, flour and salt.
Drain potatoes, pressing out all liquid.
Beat potatoes into batter.
Melt butter with oil in large skillet.
Spoon heaping tablespoons of batter into skillet, spreading batter with the back of spoon into 4-inch rounds.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and spices; sift together.
Add nuts and fruit; toss lightly.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add pumpkin. Add flour mixture and water; mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: chili and rice skillet
directions: Brown meat and onion in a skillet.
Add spices, corn, green pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Blend in sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayo, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and onion together.
Spread on a glass plate.
Top with 1 jar seafood cocktail sauce.
Spread crab meat on top (use fancy white, drained).
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serve with Club crackers.

title: pork chop and potato scallop
directions: Brown chops.
Blend soup, water, sour cream and parsley. Alternate layer of seasoned potatoes and sauce in 2-quart casserole, top with chops.
Cover and bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon size into bowl of confectioners sugar and form into a ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pinto bean and feta cheese quesadillas
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in processor.
Using on/off turns, process until very chunky puree forms.
Transfer to bowl. Season with salt and pepper.
(Can prepare 1 day ahead, cover and chill.) Place 1 tortilla on work space.
Spread with 1/4 of the bean mixture. Top with 2 tablespoons cheese, then another tortilla. Heat heavy medium skillet over medium heat.

Brush with oil. Add quesadilla. Cook until beans are heated and tortillas are brown, about 4 minutes on each side. Transfer to warm plate and cover to keep warm. Repeat with remaining tortillas, bean mixture, then cheese. Cut each quesadilla into 8 wedges and serve.
Serves 8.

title: party salad
directions: When Jell-O has set up and firmed, layer the top of Jell-O with marshmallows, bananas and pineapple.

title: bacon cheese ring
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain well and crumble into small pieces. In a medium mixing bowl, combine bacon, cheese, green onions, mayonnaise and cayenne pepper; mix thoroughly. Place almonds in the bottom of an oiled 7-cup ring mold; press cheese mixture into mold. Refrigerate overnight. Un-mold cheese ring onto platter. Place a small custard cup with strawberry preserves in the center of the ring. Serve with crackers or French bread slices. Yield 20 - 25 servings.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 350 oven 45 minutes covered. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs well. Add rest of ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: black-eyed peas and cornmeal dumplings
directions: Cook peas in a large pot with water and pork seasonings until tender and good tasting.
When done, add, if necessary, enough boiling water to bring liquid 1/2 inch above level of peas.
Have them boiling to receive dumplings as follows:
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together in a bowl.
Blend in cornmeal and parsley.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Set aside.
Put cold water in a large bowl.
Add egg yolks.
Beat until light.

Add sugar and beat 7 minutes (do not fail here; this is the secret of a light cake). Sift flour twice. Add baking powder and salt. Add dry ingredients to egg yolk mixture. Add egg whites. Fold carefully and add vanilla.
Pour into ungreased tube pan and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: quick boiled custard
directions: Mix sugar and milk together and then pudding.
Stir; add vanilla.
When ready to serve, add 1/2 to 3/4 cup milk (however thin you like it).
This is good and easy to make.
I always add more milk.

title: senator russell's sweet potatoes
directions: Put first 6 mixed ingredients into casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and put topping on casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and potato mix
directions: In a crock-pot, layer the ingredients.
Cook 6 to 8 hours on low or 4 to 5 hours on high.

title: cocktail sandwiches
directions: Cut white bread in a circle using a doughnut cutter or a small glass.
Mix mayonnaise and onions and spread evenly on circles. Put two circles together to form a sandwich.
Spread outside edge with mayonnaise and roll edges in the parsley.
Makes 22 sandwiches.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Debone chicken.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix dressing, butter and broth. Pour over top.
Brown in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice-chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add garlic.
Dissolve bouillon in water.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake, covered, for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Stir mixture occasionally.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bake 1 can of biscuits and cool.
Pour milk over torn apart biscuits.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Add sugar, eggs, melted butter and vanilla.
Pour into pan greased with butter.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Top with vanilla ice cream or fruit compote for a great dessert!

title: baby carrots
directions: Bring all to a boil.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until tender.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix strawberries, pecans, eggs, oil, vanilla and butter extract together.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well. Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour. Add rest of ingredients and mix. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: salad with a tang
directions: Cook and stir egg, mustard, vinegar and salt constantly until hot.
Add all ingredients, including heated mixture to whipped cream and sugar.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: aebleskiver (danish pancakes)(you must have a special aebleskiver pan to make these.)
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and salt; mix well.
Add flour, soda and baking powder together.
Mix well.
Fold in stiffly-beaten egg whites last.
Heat an aebleskiver pan over medium to medium-high heat.
Add a little of the melted mixture to each hole in the pan. Fill each 2/3 full with batter.
Turn as they cook with a potato nail or short skewer, so they form round balls once they are done cooking.
These are traditionally served sprinkled with powdered sugar, but we usually add the regular pancake toppings.

title: oven sweet dill pickles
directions: In each quart jar, put one head of dill on bottom and one on top.
Add 1 to 2 garlic cloves and 2 slices of onion.
Fill jars with cucumbers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and make into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.

title: green and red tomato salad(this is a great way to use both green and red tomatoes)
directions: Cube tomatoes.
Cut onion into thin slices and separate into rings.
Combine tomatoes and onion with basil in salad bowl.

title: baked limas and ham
directions: Drain 1/2 liquid off beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: parsley rice
directions: Saute onion in hot oil in large skillet until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add rice, soup and mushrooms.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix the margarine, water and salt together until almost boiling.
Add flour, the eggs, one at a time, the grated cheese (I use Monterey Jack) and the crumbled bacon.
Bake in greased pan at 275° for approximately 45 minutes.
Cut in pieces.

title: onion rings
directions: Separate onion slices into rings; soak in cold water for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, beat flour, egg, milk, sugar, salt and shortening together.
Drain onions and pat dry. With fork, dip rings into batter.
Preheat oil to 375°.
Fry in at least 1-inch of oil a few at a time for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in oven while frying remaining rings.

title: orange pineapple sherbet(makes 4 quarts)
directions: Boil the sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Remove from the stove and set aside to cool.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Freeze.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak quick-cooking oatmeal in boiling water.
Cream butter and white and brown sugars.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Combine dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal; mix well.

title: delicious pineapple cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding mix in a large mixing bowl. Mix together remaining ingredients and add to the first mixture. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookie bar
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs and extract.
Beat well.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts (optional) and chips.
Bake at 350° in large jelly roll pan for 25 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes, dust with powdered sugar and then cut into bars.

title: banana pudding
directions: Place a layer of vanilla wafers in bottom of a 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add a layer of bananas, then a layer of pudding (sour cream and all puddings are mixed together).
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: pineapple carrot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Put vinegar in cup; add pineapple juice and water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add to jello. Add the rest of ingredients.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until it begins to thicken; slowly add Wesson oil, grated onion and poppy seed.
Good on cole slaw, fruit salad or strawberries.

title: garbanzo dip
directions: Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: maple biscuit ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 12 cup fluted tube pan. In medium saucepan, melt margarine; stir in brown sugar, nuts and syrup.
Pour 1/4 cup sugar mixture into prepared pan.
Separate biscuit dough into 20 biscuits.
Stand biscuits on edge, slightly overlapping around pan.
Pour remaining sugar mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm. Makes 1 coffee cake; 10 servings.

title: congealed fruit jello salad
directions: Mix jello, cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Put hot water over this; mix well, then put the juice of a can of cocktail, plus enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Mix all this together.
Put this in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 5-inch container. Place in refrigerator 1/2 to 3/4 hour, or until it begins to set up.
Take out of refrigerator.
Mix the fruit cocktail, marshmallows and nuts with the other mixture.
Replace container in refrigerator until it "sets up."
This makes enough to serve 6 to 8 people.

title: cucumbers with sour cream
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the sour cream, sugar, vinegar, dill, pepper, salt and celery seed; blend.
Pare the cucumbers and slice as thin as possible.
Clean the onion, but slice it by hand, a bit thicker than the cucumbers.
Add the vegetables to the sour cream mixture and toss lightly.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours so the cucumbers can absorb the dressing.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil and vinegar in large bowl and stir well. Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir to coat all vegetables. Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Serve with slotted spoon. Keeps well.

title: peanut goo
directions: Beat egg whites well.
Stir other ingredients into egg whites. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased pan.
Bake until light brown.

title: my mom's mustard spread
directions: Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick. Cool.
Very good on ham sandwiches.

title: snow peas with sesame
directions: Place pea pods and carrot in a strainer.
Set the strainer in a sink.
Pour boiling water over vegetables for about 1 minute, then pat dry.
Place vegetables in a medium-size bowl and stir in orange rind, oil and seed.
Serve warm or at room temperature. Makes 4 servings.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degrees. Mix bread crumbs, parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in butter and then into remaining ingredients. Place in a shallow pan. Pour remaining mixture over chicken.

title: string beans vinaigrette
directions: Drop beans in boiling water.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain. Combine everything except tomatoes and olives.
Toss and chill all day or overnight.
Add tomatoes and black olives.
Serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, oats, eggs, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; mix well.
On wax paper, press meat mixture into 20 x 10 1/2-inch rectangle.
Combine cream cheese and chiles; mix well.
Spread cream cheese mixture over meat mixture to within 1-inch of outer edge.
Roll jelly roll fashion, starting at narrow end.
Place in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with salsa and continue baking 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: asparagus, george style
directions: In large frying pan, heat butter and oil.
Saut garlic, stirring for about 5 minutes or until it begins to turn light brown.
Add asparagus and saut for about 5 minutes.
The asparagus should still be tender-crisp.
Add the wine and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes, then serve.
You can also saut fresh mushrooms or onions before adding the asparagus.
Allow each to cook to desired doneness; however, the asparagus must be crisp.
If not, George won't eat it!
Any leftovers make excellent cream of asparagus soup.

title: caesar salad
directions: Clean and tear lettuce. Set aside. Mix together well the garlic, anchovies, oil and vinegar. Season with pepper, Worcestershire, lemon juice and oregano. Add beaten egg. Wait until ready to serve before tossing dressing on lettuce. Add Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: green rice
directions: Boil spinach in 4 1/2 cups water with bouillon; set aside. Heat the oil in a saucepan over medium heat; add the onion, garlic, celery, green pepper, scallions, chili pepper, 1 teaspoon parsley and 1 teaspoon cilantro.
Saute until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add rice and salt; saute for 5 more minutes.
Add spinach and water, bring to a boil and stir once.
Reduce heat to low, cover tightly and simmer for 25 minutes.
Garnish with the rest of cilantro and parsley, green peas and Parmesan cheese.

title: scrambled eggs in pita pockets
directions: Wrap bread in aluminum foil; bake at 350° for 15 minutes until warm.
Meanwhile, in bowl with whisk, beat eggs.
Stir in soup and vegetable; set aside.

title: family goulash
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box, except use half the amount of water and salt.
While noodles cook, cook and stir ground beef and onion in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender. Drain off fat.
Stir in drained noodles, celery, catsup, mushrooms (with liquid), tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel rolls
directions: In saucepan, boil this about 2 minutes.
Put in cake pan and put in rolls.
Pat rolls down a little, let rise to top of pan and bake about 30 minutes at 350° until golden.
Cool so caramel doesn't run off rolls.
Turn out onto wax paper or tinfoil.
I use a bar pan; then you better eat 1 or 2 because when everyone finds out they are done they are gone!

title: grandma jeffer's sour cream cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cool lemon salad
directions: Cut fruit into bite-size pieces.
Prepare pudding according to the package directions.
Fold in the Cool Whip and gently fold in the drained fruit.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside. In a mixer bowl, beat sugar and shortening with electric mixer until light, scraping sides of bowl often.
Add eggs, one at a time and the milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately to creamed mixture, beating until smooth.
Fold in nuts.
Turn batter into a lightly greased 4 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 60 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add sauce.
Meantime, boil noodles according to directions and drain.

title: jack souffle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use loaf pan.
Slice Jack cheese and layer bottom of pan with 1/2 of Jack cheese.
Add 1/2 of spinach to cheese, add cottage cheese then rest of spinach.
Add remaining Jack cheese slices on top.

title: no bake cookies
directions: For Orange Blossom Cookies:
Use 1 small can orange juice concentrate.

title: egg-sausage souffle
directions: Place precooked turkey and spaghetti in a casserole large enough to accommodate your needs.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place drained asparagus, crushed tomatoes and diced onion in 8 x 8-inch buttered casserole dish.
Crumble bacon and cheese on top.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes or until hot.
This casserole is also good served cold.

title: s'mores
directions: Take a graham cracker, put a piece of Hershey bar on top, then put a large marshmallow on that. Put in microwave until the marshmallow melts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread steamed broccoli in casserole dish.
Mix soup, cheese, onion, milk and 1/2 the bread crumbs together.
Pour over broccoli. Top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt.
Add rind, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add milk and beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake.

title: christmas limas
directions: Thaw lima beans until they will break apart.
Place them in a greased casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add pimento; dot with butter.
Add water.
Cover; bake at 425° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: easy fluffy frosting
directions: Beat well the oleo, sugar and shortening.
Add flour and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well on high speed until fluffy.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil carrots (sliced) until just tender.
Melt butter; add Velveeta, Tabasco and onion; stir until cheese melts.
Add butter cheese mix to drained carrots.
Place in buttered casserole. Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly about 20 minutes.

title: deviled beef toss
directions: In large salad bowl, toss together romaine and iceberg lettuce.
Arrange beef strips, halved and whole cherry tomatoes, onion rings and anchovies on greens.
Serve with Mustard-Horseradish Dressing (to follow).

title: sugar-free party mix
directions: Melt candy coating in microwave.
Pour over cereal mixture; stir until all is coated.
Let cool and break apart.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
Combine juice, sugar, eggs, salt and cook until slightly thickened.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients and freeze in 9 inch pan.

title: five hour oven stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Place meat and vegetables in 12 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle salt, onion soup mix, tapioca and sugar over vegetables.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 5 hours.
Don't peek while baking because that lets steam out.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dilly casserole onion bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in mixing bowl, cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill, salt, baking soda, egg and yeast.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in warm place (50 to 60 minutes). Stir down dough and turn into greased 8 inch round casserole (1 1/2 or 2 quart).
Let rise in warm place until light (30 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed; put about 1/2 inch high mayonnaise.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of sugar on top of mayonnaise. Chill overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all together and use to baste chicken, follow with finishing sauce.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill.
May form into ball or place in loaf pan.
After chilled, unmold.
If made into ball, roll in 1/2 to 1 cup more chopped nuts.
(May roll in parsley if you want.) If made in loaf pan, garnish with pineapple rings or chunks and parsley.

title: christmas salad
directions: In large bowl, combine first three ingredients.
In cup, whisk together remaining ingredients.
Pour over salad to coat.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until almost tender and drain.
Saute green pepper and onion in 1/2 stick of butter.
Place cabbage in buttered casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix sauce with pepper and onion; pour over cabbage.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain peas, corn, water chestnuts and pimientos; combine.
Add celery, onion and green pepper, along with salt and pepper. Combine oil, sugar, vinegar and water; pour over vegetable mixture.
Let marinate for several hours.

title: microwave fish
directions: Mix the crackers and margarine together.
Place the fish in a microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Top with the cracker or bread crumb mix.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Heat on High for 9 to 11 minutes, turning once at 5 minutes.
Fish is done when it is light and flaky, just as baked fish in an oven.
Serves 4.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix lard and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add cream or milk, vanilla, flour and baking powder; mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Press down with glass dipped in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: microwave pizza muffins
directions: Split muffins in half.
Top each half with 1 to 2 tablespoons pizza sauce, 2 of the garnishes, Italian seasoning and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Arrange 2 pizzas on a paper plate in the microwave for 2 to 3 minutes on Medium-high or until the cheese is melted.

title: pasta and broccoli
directions: Boil pasta according to package. During last 5 minutes, add broccoli to pasta.
Meanwhile, saute garlic and red pepper in oil. Drain pasta and broccoli; reserve the 1/2 cup water.
Toss broccoli and pasta with water and oil.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend squash in blender.
If large, remove seeds and pulp. Mix eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and squash.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stracciatela(roman egg soup)
directions: Bring the broth to a boil in a saucepan.
In a bowl, beat together the eggs, breadcrumbs and cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove broth from heat and pour in the egg mixture, blending well with a whisk.
Return the broth to a bowl, stirring constantly, with a whisk.

title: pork roast with glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and cinnamon. Rub into meat. Place roast on rack in baking oven, fat side up. Bake about 3 to 3 1/2 hours. Allow 25 minutes per pound. Place potatoes around roast and continue baking, spooning off fat.

title: slovak easter cheese
directions: Beat eggs lightly so yolks are broken.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Put into 2-quart casserole and bake in oven about 30 minutes at 350° or until consistency of custard. Spoon into cheesecloth.
Squeeze and tie tightly with cord.
Hang from an object until well drained, several hours or overnight. When dried, remove from cheesecloth and refrigerate.
Slice and serve with ham.

title: butter beans, bacon and tomatoes
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients. Stir in tomatoes and simmer 3 minutes. Stir in broth and butter beans. Bring to a boil and continue simmering covered for 30 minutes. Remove lid and simmer 20 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients and cook additional 5 minutes.
Good with rice!

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add onion.
Cook until tender; stir in tomato paste, water, garlic and seasonings.
Simmer 30 minutes.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, layer noodles with meat mixture and cheeses. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: coquito
directions: With a hammer or mallet, crack open the coconuts.
They should break into several pieces.
Place pieces in the oven and heat for 5 minutes at a low setting.
This will make it easier to remove the coconut skin from the shell.
With a small paring knife, remove coconut from the shell.
Discard shell.

title: scallop and bacon linguine
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet over medium-high heat until crisp. Transfer bacon to large serving bowl.
Discard all but 1 tablespoon drippings from skillet.
Add minced shallots and sea scallops. Cook until browned, 4 minutes.
Transfer scallops to bowl.
Add clam juice to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Toss with cooked linguine, bacon, scallops, parsley and olive oil.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli 2 to 3 hours.
Put in buttered dish. Melt 1 stick butter and Velveeta cheese.
Pour mixture over broccoli. Add a layer of shredded cheese.
Melt 1 stick butter and add approximately 30 to 35 crumbled Ritz cheese crackers.
Pour on top of broccoli and cheese.
Add another layer of shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Thaw bread dough and roll each loaf out flat.
Use half of ingredients on each loaf.
Place ingredients on half of the flat bread dough.
Fold over and bake at 350° until bread is golden brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour a large 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 1 large can crushed pineapple over bottom of pan.
Cover with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle 1 package dry cake mix (yellow or white) on top.
Melt 2 sticks of margarine or butter and pour over cake. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. (Check cake for doneness.)

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Open and drain asparagus spears.
Lay in dish; cover with Italian dressing.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix well, then pour over the cream cheese layer.
Top with 8 ounces of Cool Whip, then refrigerate.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale. Freeze. Let thaw slightly before serving. Before serving, add ginger ale.

title: crabmeat delight
directions: Thaw crabmeat and squeeze out all water.
Break in chunks. Melt cheese and butter in double boiler.
Add crabmeat chunks to cheese and butter mixture.
Mix well.
Serve warm in chafing dish. Serve on large bread wafers or any large wafer that isn't seasoned, as you want to enjoy the flavor of the crabmeat mixture.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Cream sugars, oil and egg. Sift dry ingredients together. Add with all the rest. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream.
Combine 2 together.
Layer with graham crackers and bananas.
Refrigerate.

title: quick skillet chili
directions: Brown meat in fat in skillet.
Brown pepper and onion.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: a really delicious recipe
directions: Take the onion, preferably a Vidalia.
Peel the onion and quarter 3/4 of the way down the onion.
Cut a cup shaped depression in the top of the onion.
Place a piece of margarine on top of onion and salt and pepper.
Place in microwave for 5 to 8 minutes. Cover with waxed paper.
This is a great tasty treat.

title: cherry cream torte
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy. Slowly beat in sugar and vanilla. Beat until glossy. Fold in crushed soda crackers and chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool completely. Spread Cool Whip over top. Spoon Comstock cherry pie filling over top. Chill before serving.

title: sauce gribiche(tartar sauce)
directions: Blend all ingredients together and refrigerate. It is very good with cold leftover fish.

title: microwave cheese dip
directions: Mix together and microwave until bubbly.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Cream the shortening. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.,
Add molasses, egg and vinegar.
Mix well. Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Stir well. Add to molasses mixture, stirring well. Shape dough into a ball and knead until smooth.
Chill overnight.
Divide dough in half. Roll each half of dough to 1/4 to 1/8-inch thickness on a floured board.
Use cookie cutter for desired shape.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until browned.

title: noodles with pesto sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Place well drained noodles or spaghetti in large bowl.
Pour sauce over all and toss lightly to cover. Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Combine last 6 ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Top with browned pork chops and onions.
Cover casserole and cook 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
This works real good in a crock-pot.

title: cappuccino mixfort collins, colorado
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container.

title: speedy egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then add scalded milk.
Bake in a very hot 475° oven for 5 minutes.
Then bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: carrots lyonnaise
directions: Pare carrots and slice in julienne strips or bias circles. Cook carrots in bouillon, covered, for 10 minutes.
Melt butter. Add onions and cook, covered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in next 4 ingredients; bring to boiling.
Add carrots and stock and simmer, uncovered, to blend flavors.
Add pinch of sugar and a shake or two of dried or fresh dill weed.

title: pecan pie cookies(christmas cookies)
directions: Stir butter or margarine and sugar on low speed in large bowl of electric mixer.
Add syrup and egg yolks; beat until thoroughly blended.
Stir in flour gradually.
Chill several hours.
Beat egg whites slightly.
Using 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie, roll into balls.
Brush very slightly with egg white.
Place on greased cookie sheet, leaving a 2-inch space between each cookie. Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix together and chill for 24 hours.

title: hot pretzels
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups more flour, then knead the dough until it is no longer sticky.
Let rise in a greased bowl until it doubles in size. Punch it down; divide it into 12 pieces.
Roll each piece into an 18-inch rope.
Twist each rope into a pretzel shape and place on a greased baking sheet.
Let them double in size again.
Bring 4 cups water and 4 tablespoons baking soda to a boil in a large pan. (The pan should not be aluminum.)
Place each pretzel in the water (one by one) and remove when it floats.
Place it back on the baking sheet; sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake for 12 minutes in a preheated oven at 475°.
Eat while warm.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer 1:
One head romaine lettuce and 1 package fresh spinach.

title: oven scrambled eggs
directions: Slightly beat eggs; add milk and salt.
Mix well.
Melt butter in large shallow cake pan.
Add eggs.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Stir once after 20 minutes.
Serves about 20 people.

title: fluffy frozen peanut pie
directions: May use graham crumb crust or any pie crust, cooked.

title: zeke's chili(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Brown beef and half of onion.
Drain off grease.
Mix everything together in crock-pot, breaking up tomatoes with hands. Cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix ingredients of First Part and boil 5 minutes. Add Second Part well mixed and boil 5 minutes more. Be sure and add the flour the last thing.

title: chicken spectacular casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked rice.
Pour into well-greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in freezer until icy.
To serve, spoon into glasses and top with 7-Up or ginger ale. Garnish with fresh strawberries when available.

title: quick tater tot bake
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onion; drain off any fat.
Season and place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with Tater Tots. Combine soup with milk or water; pour over Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana boat
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions; fold in Cool Whip.
Line pie pan with vanilla wafers.
Pour one half of pudding/Cool Whip over wafers.
Add bananas and cover with rest of mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Dissolve cornstarch and mustard in vinegar.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Can be used over chicken, spareribs and hamburgers.

title: spinach souffle quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Could be 40 minutes.) Serves 4 to 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and peppers until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add cooked noodles and other ingredients except cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.
Top with Velveeta cheese slices. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash grapes and dry.
Cook milk, butter, and cornstarch until thick.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add grapes, pineapple and pecans.
Chill at least 24 hours before serving.

title: beer meat balls
directions: Mix ground round, bread crumbs, eggs and milk into meat balls. Brown.
Simmer in the following sauce:

title: hot brussels sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts until soft and add chopped onion, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cook until hot.
Add bread cubes at the very end and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: cherry confetti pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in pie filling.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pastry shells.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast in fat in heavy skillet; pour off excess fat. Place tomatoes and garlic bud in blender and blend well.
Add brown sugar and dissolve into liquid.
Add to pot.
Add celery, bell pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and vinegar. Cook 8 to 10 hours in iron pot or slow cooker until meat falls apart when moved with a fork.
Add 4 or 5 carrots and potatoes. Continue cooking until vegetables are done.
Cook, uncovered, until sauce thickens.
Six or eight prunes or peaches (which have been soaked in water) may be added to the pot in the last 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: pink bavarian cream
directions: Drain strawberries; reserve syrup.
Pour boiling water over jello; stir until dissolved.
Add enough cold water to reserved syrup to measure 1 cup; stir into dissolved jello.
Chill until almost set.

title: bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the 3 cans of beans, green pepper and onion.
Mix well the vinegar, salad oil, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over beans.
Chill well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chipped ham foil sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients; fill buns and wrap in foil.
Heat 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: egg noodles
directions: Combine eggs and salt.
Beat until foamy.
Add butter and flour; mix well.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out very thin; cut into 1/4-inch pieces about 4 inches long.
Spread out on a floured board.
Cook until tender.

title: texas chicken casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
In a casserole dish, layer starting with tortillas, chicken, soup and cheese.
Repeat.
Freeze for later on or bake at 375° until hot throughout.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook fryer in pressure cooker until done.
Cool.
Remove bones and skin; break into pieces.
Cook noodles in broth from chicken until done.
If too much broth, drain, then add both cans of soup and chicken.
Place in baking dish sprayed with Pam and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: spicy nibbles
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss well and set aside.
Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce and seasoning mix in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until margarine melts and mixture is smooth. Drizzle over cracker mixture and toss well.
Spread mixture in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes or until crisp, stirring twice.
Cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Pour into large deep dish.
Bake 1 hour at medium heat (375°).

title: kerry's green chili
directions: Take your pork tenderloins and pound them out with a meat hammer.
Then add salt, pepper, some soy sauce, and a little water so they do not dry out and wrap them in foil.
Bake in the oven on about 325 for an hour.
Take the tenderloin out and cut or chop into small pieces.
In a large skillet melt your butter then add your onions and saute them for about 10 min.
Next add your green chilies and saute them for about 10 min.
In a bowl place your flour, salt and pepper and add just enough vegetable oil so the mixture is not hard to stir but not runny.
Add this mixture to your chili and stir in real good for about 2-3 min.
Get a large soup pot and transfer the chili begin adding your heated beef broth, diced tomatoes, pork and garlic.
Cook on medium low heat for about 4 hours stirring every 15 to 20 min. so it does not burn. AND DON'T FORGET THE WINE.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, butter, cocoa and milk for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting when mixture reaches a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Good for kids to make.

title: deep-fried wonton cookies(teem gok)
directions: Mix prunes, apricots, brown sugar, coconut and almonds.
Place about 2 teaspoons filling on center of each wonton skin.
Moisten edges with water.
Fold each skin in half to form triangle; press edges firmly to seal.
(Cover to prevent drying.)
Heat oil (1 to 1 1/2 inches) to 360°.
Fry 3 to 4 wontons at a time, turning occasionally, until golden brown, about 1 minute on each side. Drain on paper towels.
Store in airtight container.
Serve with ice cream or sherbet.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Do not salt.
Pick chicken off bone and put aside.
Save broth.
Melt margarine and stir into dressing.
In a greased casserole dish, put a layer of margarine and stir into dressing.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent, not brown. Add cubed/washed potatoes in cooked onions. Cover with water only to top of potatoes. Cover and cook on medium heat until potatoes are soft (keep checking). Add cans of clams (minced or chopped) with the juice to the potato/onion mixture. Stir. Now add tomato soup, salt and pepper; stir again and heat through until hot. Easy and delicious! Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine (or use oil); add sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add potatoes.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices.

title: grandma's old fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Add first 4 ingredients and stir.
Add flour until mixture can be rolled out on floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 325° oven.

title: mostaccioli alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine whipping cream and butter in a Dutch oven or saucepan.
Heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally (do not boil).
Add cheese and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Add pasta and toss well.
Serve immediately.

title: applelicious cake
directions: Grease a spring-form pan.
In mixer bowl, put cake mix.
Add cinnamon and vegetable oil.
Mix on low until crumbly.
Remove 3/4 cup of mixture.
Set aside.
Add eggs to mix and applesauce.
Mix well with mixture.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In a large pan, combine popcorn, M&M's and peanuts.
Set aside.
Combine margarine, oil and marshmallows in a large saucepan.
Cook until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over popcorn mixture and stir until well mixed.
Lightly spray a Bundt pan with Pam.
Press mixture into pan.
Remove and place on a cake plate.

title: three hour salad
directions: Bring water to boil and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Mix in the other ingredients.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients
except
chicken.
Fold in chicken (add 1/2 to 3/4
cup chicken broth if mixture seems dry).
Mix crushed cornflakes
and
butter, sprinkle on top.
Almonds are optional. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered ham and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Coarsely chop onion.
Cut ham into 1/2 inch cubes.
In a food processor fitted with a slicing blade, cut potatoes into 1/4 inch thick slices.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, onion, ham and flour.
Toss to distribute ingredients evenly.
Spread the mixture in prepared baking dish.
In a small bowl, beat milk, mustard, salt and pepper together.
Pour the milk mixture over vegetables and ham in the dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover dish with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 45 minutes longer or until top is brown and potatoes are tender.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well until thoroughly blended. Roll into party size balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes about 100 party balls.

title: quick cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients together, mixing well.
Using a teaspoon, drop small balls into powdered sugar, rolling them to coat.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: almond fudge topped shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar and salt until fluffy.
Mix in flour.
With floured hands, press into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with condensed milk, stirring constantly, until all chips are melted.
Stir in almond extract.
Spread evenly over shortbread.
Sprinkle on almonds, then press them down firmly. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Can be stored at room temperature.

title: bohemian omelets
directions: Prepare prune mix from 3 1/2 ounces fresh prunes, 3 1/2 ounces sugar and a small amount of water by slowly roasting mix in the oven, then blending and pureeing it and gently flavoring with dark rum.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix together in pan.
Cook this mixture until it thickens and looks clear, doesn't take long.
If you cook this too long, it will taste strong.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir 15 minutes before serving.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in refrigerator until time to use.

title: taco spread
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, avocado and picante sauce until creamy.
Spread over a platter that is about 9 x 9-inches. Sprinkle the onion, green pepper, tomato and Cheddar cheese over the creamy mixture.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Great for parties.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop and drain vegetables.
Add vinegar and mustard.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add flour, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Cook 10 minutes; cool.
Add mayonnaise.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until golden.
Combine soup, water and Cheez Whiz.
Cook broccoli; then drain.
Mix broccoli with onion and celery.
Combine everything.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle a little Cheddar on top if desired for taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes uncovered.
If using glass dish, lower heat to 325°.

title: sweet 'n sour beef
directions: Brown meat.
Chop vegetables and mix together in crock-pot. Cook on low overnight.
Before eating, add cornstarch to some water and thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: granma edna's pasta dough
directions: In large bowl, stir flour with oil, salt, eggs and 1/4 cup water to make a stiff dough.
On well-floured surface, knead dough until smooth and not sticky, about 20 times.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rest for 30 minutes.
Use noodle cutter or cut with knife into noodles (flour well).

title: fantastic peanut butter icing
directions: Mix about 2 minutes.

title: sue's salsa
directions: Add tomatoes to blender to chop (zap blender on and off to chop).
Mix well.
Make a day ahead.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and tapioca together.
Add water, then bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes. Add Jell-O.
Cool, then add sliced peaches.
Pour into the two baked pie shells.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lemon parsley halibut(microwaved)
directions: Melt butter or margarine and add all other ingredients except halibut fillets.
Mix until smooth. Coat halibut fillets on both sides and place in glass baking dish.
Pour remaining butter mixture over top. Cover and microwave on High for about 4 minutes per inch of thickness of fish or until the fish flakes easily.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake butter cake mix according to package directions in a buttered 9
x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 can Eagle Brand milk and 1 can cream of coconut thoroughly.
Poke holes in cake with a fork while cake is still hot from oven.
Pour milk and coconut mixture slowly over cake.
Frost with Cool Whip just before serving and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate leftovers!
Yum!

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Cook peas and drain.
Mix all ingredients except noodles. Chill 1 hour or more.
Toss with noodles just before serving. Serves 4.

title: pillsbury chewy crescent bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Unroll crescent dough; place rectangles in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Gently press dough to cover bottom of pan; seal the perforations.
Pour condensed milk evenly over dough.
Sprinkle with frosting mix.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown. Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen bars.
Twenty-Five dollar Bake-off winner.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground chuck, sausage, onion, green pepper, celery, oats, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and sage in bowl; mix well.
Add tomato juice and egg; mix well.
Shape into loaf and place in 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer or until brown.
May make gravy from meat loaf broth.
May substitute bread crumbs for oats and V-8 juice for tomato juice.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: panned cabbage
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy pan over medium heat.
Add cabbage and water.
Cover pan tightly.
Cook over low heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6. Contains 50 calories and 4 g fat per serving.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth.
Cut into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sliced apples in greased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples and bake until apples are soft.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, beat until fluffy.
Add oil; mix dry ingredients and add.
Pour most of batter into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling over batter.
Pour remaining batter over top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
When cool, drizzle with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put all ingredients (except soda and peanuts) into boiler and bring to a boil.
Add 2 cups raw peanuts and cook until the mixture is a light honey color (the peanuts will crack and pop).
Remove from heat; add soda and stir quickly.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
When cold, push up from the bottom of cookie sheet and brittle will break up.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; set aside liquid. In a medium mixing bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky. Stir in flour. Add
baking powder to reserved salmon liquid and then add to salmon mixture. Form into small patties. Drop in Crisco and fry until golden brown, about 5 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper until onion is tender.
Stir in rice, chestnuts, mushrooms and soy sauce.

title: smothered quail
directions: Rinse quail well.
Pat	dry
with paper towels.
In hot butter, in large skillet,
saute
quail
until nicely browned, about 10 minutes.
Add
shallots; cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 5
minutes.
Add
vinegar, sugar and salt, mixing
well.
Bring to
boiling.	Reduce	heat
and
simmer, tightly covered, 20 to 30
minutes	or until quail are tender. Serve quail with pan juices spooned over.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut centers from peppers and boil in salted water for about 10 minutes; drain.
Brown onion in margarine and then add salt, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and ground beef.
Allow meat to brown.
Add rice and cheese.
Add tomatoes and egg to mixture; toss well and stuff into peppers, putting the remainder of mixture around peppers in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In it combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook over medium heat to 236° (soft ball stage) about 12 minutes, stirring frequently.
(Mixture should boil gently over entire surface.)
Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients and stir until chocolate is melted.
Turn into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Score while warm; cut when firm.
Chill, if necessary.
Makes about 3 1/2 pounds.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Put raw rice in bottom of casserole.
Brown pork chops and place on top of rice.
Arrange one slice tomato, onion and bell pepper on each pork chop.
Pour bouillon over all and add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stilton-mill feuille
directions: Place the raisins in the Port wine and marinate them for 1/2 hour. Drain the raisins and gently pat them dry with paper towels. Place the Stilton cheese in a food processor and blend it. Add the softened butter and blend it in. Add the heavy cream and blend it in until the mixture is very smooth. Remove the mixture from the food processor and place it in a bowl. Add the marinated raisins and mix them in well.

title: bouquet garni vinegar
directions: Bring vinegar to a boil in small nonaluminum saucepan. Meanwhile, place herbs in a clean hot 16-ounce jar or bottle. Pour hot vinegar into jars.
Cover and let stand for several days. Ready to be used.
Store in cool place.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in large 9 x
9-inch
baking
pan
(I
use a 10-inch frying pan).
Spread brown sugar evenly in pan and when beginning to caramelize slightly,
arrange pineapple slices and fill center of pineapple with
maraschino cherries and the nuts between
the
other areas
as
desired.
Sift
together
flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat
egg	yolks
until
light, adding sugar gradually. Add
pineapple
juice
and sifted flour alternately and beat well.	Fold in
stiffly
beaten
egg whites and blend
well.
Pour batter
over
pineapple
mixture.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cake should spring back when lightly touched in center.
Turn	upside down on cake plate (cover pan with cake	plate
before turning upside down). Serves 8.

title: swedish meat balls(makes 48 balls)
directions: Combine meats and salt; blend lightly.
Add crumbs that have been soaked in water, then drained.
Stir in allspice, nutmeg and onion.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in butter.
Add water to cover.
Cover pan; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add bouillon cubes; stir until dissolved.
If desired, thicken sauce.
(I put meat balls in large roasting pan and cook in oven.)

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water only until leaves fall off head. Reserve 14 to 16 large leaves for rolls and set remaining cabbage aside.
Combine rice, beef, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup soup; mix well.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons meat mixture on each cabbage leaf.
Fold in sides, starting at an unfolded edge.
Roll up leaf completely to enclose meat

title: creamy chocolate cupcakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into 18 greased or paper-lined muffin cups.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel avocados and mash well.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Let set for at least 1 hour.
Serve cold.

title: bonnie's televara(an old irish recipe)
directions: Brown ground meat with chopped onion, pepper and celery. Season with salt, pepper (a dash of garlic salt, too).
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Layer in casserole:
noodles, ground meat mixture, cream-style corn, tomatoes and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Just keep layering until all ingredients are used.
This makes 2 medium casseroles with 2 layers in each.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until heated through.

title: mock boursin
directions: Unwrap cream cheese and place in a glass mixing bowl. Microwave, uncovered, about 1 1/2 minutes on 50% power (Medium) or until softened but not melted.
Blend in garlic, caraway seed, basil, dill and chives.
Pat into a round cake, about 1 1/2-inches high.
Roll generously on all sides in lemon pepper.
Refrigerate. Best made a few days ahead so that flavors blend.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: easy pie pastry
directions: Melt margarine in pie plate.
Sift flour and sugar; pat out. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough onto pizza pan and bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Spread cream cheese on top.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Spread over cookie and cream cheese.
Chill 4 hours.
Cut into pizza slices.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Mix together orange juice, boiling water and dates in a bowl. Stir in
soda,
sugar,
shortening and vanilla.
Add an egg, then flour
sifted
with baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts.	Bake in	greased
loaf
pan
for
50 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: bacalhau(codfish balls)
directions: Boil codfish with garlic and parsley until done.
Drain and cool; flake and add onion, parsley and pepper flakes.
Boil potatoes and mash them.
Stir potatoes into codfish mixture with one beaten egg.
Form into generous 1-inch balls or small patties (for fish cakes) and deep fry.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat until thick and lemon colored (5 minutes) the 3 large eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and beat only until smooth and well blended.
Grease shallow pan (10 x 15-inch), then line with wax paper and grease paper.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Turn immediately onto wax paper which is sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove pan paper and spread with jelly or jam; roll in wax paper until cool.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in 1/2 clam juice and 1/2 water.
Add clams just before potatoes are done.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Remove half the juice.

title: chicken breading
directions: Mix all ingredients together and coat chicken.
Oven bake or deep fry.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring to boil the sugar and syrup.
Let bubble.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in cereal.
Spread in greased cake pan. Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips; spread on top.
Enjoy when cooled.

title: seafood medley
directions: Saute
vegetables, shrimp and scallops in olive oil and seasonings.
Set
aside.
Broil
flounder
until
flaky.
Lay vegetables
and seafood mixture on top of flounder and broil a few more minutes.

title: walker's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Spoon bean mixture into a lightly greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours or until hot and bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Serves 12.

title: drop apple cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: johns favorite bbq sauce
directions: Cook on stove until simmering. Cover meat or chicken with sauce and bake or grill as usual.

title: swiss cheese fondue(microwave)
directions: Mix together cornstarch, wine, water and seasoning until smooth.
Microwave on High (100%) for 4 to 6 minutes or until thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in cheese until melted.
If not completely melted, microwave on High (100%) for 1 to 2 minutes or until melted.
Serve hot with French bread cubes.
Recipe yields about 3 cups.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Beat eggs in small dish.
Add eggs and all other ingredients to sugar and cocoa.
Pour into frozen 8 or 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until set.

title: microwave tomato shells stuffed with curried chicken
directions: Cut a slice from stem end of each tomato.
Scoop out pulp and invert tomatoes to drain.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole in microwave oven (30 seconds at High).
Blend in flour, onion and curry powder.
Stir in milk.
Cook uncovered for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes at High or until thickened and smooth.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in mixture of salt, pepper and garlic powder and then chicken.
Fill tomato shells with chicken mixture and place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Heat uncovered in microwave oven for 4 to 6 minutes at High or until thoroughly heated.
Rotate dish one-quarter turn once.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Bring to a boil the Jell-O, sugar and water. Add cream cheese, baby food and crushed pineapple (not drained).
Mix well with beater.
Set aside. Beat Pet milk which has been chilled.
Fold this into other mixture (after the milk has been whipped).
Spread in dish and sprinkle with pecans.
Chill!

title: old fashioned doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until light in color.
Add sugar and nutmeg; beat until light.
Add oil and stir.
Add salt and milk with the soda stirred in.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour with baking powder; beat until smooth.
Add rest of flour and dough will start to leave the spoon.
Flour the kneading board lightly, roll out and cut.
Fry in hot lard.
Recipe makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: mile high confetti pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar.

Gradually beat until stiff. Fold in almonds, cherries, syrup, vanilla and almond flavoring. Fold confectioners sugar into whipped cream. Fold into beaten egg mixture. Pour into chilled graham cracker crust. Garnish with cherry pieces and slivered almonds.
Freeze until firm.

title: avocado-crab dip
directions: Combine avocados, lemon juice, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Beat until smooth.
Add cream cheese, sour cream and salt; blend well.
Stir in drained, flaked crab meat; chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pork loin or rib chops
directions: Arrange chops in 9 x 13 pan. Place all ingredients on chops. Cover pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and cook about 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done.
Mix broccoli, egg, onion, mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Pour into 2 quart casserole baking dish.
Combine margarine and stuffing mix, then sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, butter, lemon and egg yolks.
Add milk and whites of eggs (beaten stiff).
Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Saute diced onions in butter until lightly browned.
Add cubed pork, then sauerkraut and top with cubed apples.
Add a little water and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes and pork or sausage.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put in greased casserole dish. Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Combine the soup and bouillon well.
Add the water and shrimp. Heat and just before serving, add the sherry to taste.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon brand and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set.

title: turkey 'n chive sandwich
directions: In small bowl, stir together cream cheese and chives.
Spread on roll halves.
Layer bottom half of roll with lettuce leaf, 2 slices turkey, tomato, green pepper and 1 slice cheese.
Top with remaining roll.

title: krazy kake
directions: Place sifter in 8-inch square pan and into it add flour, sugar, soda, salt, and cocoa.
Sift into pan and make 3 indentations in mixture.
In one add 1 tsp. vanilla; another add 1 Tbsp. vinegar; and in the other add 5 Tbsp. oil.
Pour in gradually, beating, 1 cup water.
Beat smooth.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cut or blend first 4 ingredients until the consistency of meal.
Add powdered milk mixture.
Roll dough to approximately 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into strips.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Approximate yield: 1 dozen.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Slice roast in at least 1/2-inch slices.
Place in crock-pot. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over meat.
Cook on high for 6 hours.
If gravy needs to be thicker, make mixture of cornstarch and water to thicken.
Roast can be cooked in oven at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours instead of crock-pot.

title: tomato relish
directions: Add all ingredients together and cook for about 25 to 30 minutes.
When it starts to boil, put in jars.

title: rice
directions: Measure rice into 2-quart saucepan with tight fitting lid. Add water and salt.
Cook until it boils up high; lower heat, cover and cook 15 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.
Let it steam a few minutes and serve.
Serves 5 to 6.
This works with any amount of rice; just double the water to keep it in proportion to the rice.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl; chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain off excess fat.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 2-quart covered casserole dish for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown beef in heavy saucepan; drain.
Chop onion and chilies; add to beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low heat for at least 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: stove top scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes, then cut them into 4 pieces longways, then slice them sideways.
Do the same with the onions.
Take a 3-quart pot and put a layer of potatoes; sprinkle pepper and garlic salt.
Put 5 cut squares of butter over the potatoes, then a layer of onions, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat until you use all the potatoes, then pour in a cup of milk.
Cook on low heat until done.

title: meat and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Make corn bread.
Place on top of meat mixture.
Bake until corn bread is done.
Check oven temperature for corn bread.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Make gravy according to directions and add cheese.
Pour over potatoes and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add milk if it thickens too much.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: mocha float
directions: Into an 8 ounce glass measure the first three ingredients. Gradually add enough club soda to fill glass 3/4 full.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add ice cream; stir.
Serve with a spoon and straw.
Serves 1.

title: extra-easy lasagna
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook beef until browned, and spoon off fat.
Add Prego mixture.
Heat thoroughly; stir often.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: *You can use tomatoes, green peppers, onions, cauliflower, cucumber and radishes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook green pepper, celery and onion in butter for five minutes.
Blend soup and milk and heat slowly. Do not boil.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Combine chicken, noodles, pimentos and mayonnaise.
Mix well and turn into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour cheese sauce over all and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil, eggs and sugar well in large bowl.
Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Beat.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 350° in round pans for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust)
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
When smooth, add eggs, milk, vanilla, coconut and margarine.
Grease with butter a 9 1/2 or 10-inch deep dish pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and fill bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add half of potatoes.
Combine soup, sour cream and milk; pour half of mixture over potatoes.
Layer 1 cup cheese.
Top with remainder of potatoes and soup mixture.
Top with 1 cup cheese and cornflake crumbs.
Add 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick scones
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, 1/3 cup milk and 1 tablespoon sugar until mixture leaves side of bowl.
Stir in cranberries.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Soften yeast in the warm milk.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour.
When bubbly add salt, beaten eggs, shortening and second amount of flour.
Knead in enough flour so it is easy to handle.
Let raise until double in bulk.
Cut off pieces and dip first in melted butter and then in mixture of sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Place one layer of balls in angel food cake pan until each barely touches the next.
Fill in cracks with raisins and additional chopped nuts.
Continue this way until all balls are placed in pan.
Cover and let raise for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
What sugar mixture is left may be sprinkled between layers of dough before baking.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt oleo; add cinnamon, brown sugar and raisins or nut meats. Mix well and spread on rolled dough.
Roll up and slice 3/4-inch thick.
Put in pan and let rise until double, about 40 to 50 minutes.
Bake.

title: country sweet potatoes
directions: Drain syrup from potatoes.
Mash; add milk, sugar, margarine and salt.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Put in shallow, greased baking dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Heat at 375° for 15 minutes or until marshmallows are brown on top.
Serves 4.

title: cashew cream
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender for one minute.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until the mixture thickens. Use as a topping the same as you would whipped cream.

title: roast pork
directions: Make slits in fat of roast; put on rack in roasting pan and baste with sauce made of the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, basting often with sauce.
Trim off a thin layer of the fat before serving.

title: macadamia nut fruitcake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; toss gently.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Combine 3/4 cup flour, soda, salt and lemon rind; gradually add to egg mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir Macadamia nut mixture into batter.
Spoon batter into a greased and wax paper lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: latkes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Put in center of a clean dish towel and squeeze out excess water.
Mix potatoes with the onion, salt and pepper.
Add eggs and enough flour to absorb the extra moisture. Heat oil in skillet until it is very hot.
Drop batter by soup spoonfuls and fry until brown.
Remove to a platt

title: baked pork chop and noodle casserole
directions: Brown chops and set aside.
Combine cooked noodles, tomatoes and onion in open baking dish.
Place chops on top of noodles. Bake at 350° until chops are thoroughly cooked.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana split cake
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients for 15 minutes. Butter pan lightly. Line pan with vanilla wafers. Spread mix over wafers. Slice the bananas lengthwise. Drain the pineapple well. Pour over other ingredients. Top with Cool Whip. Decorate with chopped pecans and cherries. Let set several hours or overnight.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Combine nuts, dates, soda and salt in a mixing bowl; add the shortening and boiling water.
Allow mixture to stand for 15 minutes.
Stir to blend.
Beat the eggs slightly.
Add the vanilla.
Stir in sugar and flour.
Add to date mixture.
Do not overmix.
Bake in 350° oven in greased and floured pan.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add evaporated milk.
In a skillet brown meat with onion.
Add tomatoes, chilies and garlic. When cheese is completely melted, add meat mixture.
Serve with Doritos.
Top with sliced jalapeno peppers (if your tongue can take it).

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain very well.
Mix all ingredients well, and shape into bite size balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cube cheese and put on top of broccoli; mix.
Crumble crackers and put on top of broccoli mixture.
Melt butter and drizzle over crackers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: In very hot jars, place first three ingredients.
Bring to boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pour boiling hot brine over pickles that are already put in the jar and seal.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix cake mix with margarine and 2/3 cup milk.
Pour half the batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
While batter bakes, melt caramels with remaining milk. Remove cake from oven, pour caramel mixture over and sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Add remaining half of batter and return to oven and bake 20 minutes.
Frost with coconut pecan icing.

title: party punch
directions: Over medium heat, mix sugar and water into a syrup.
While hot, add jello, then cool.
Add lemon juice, orange juice, pineapple juice, water and almond extract.

title: pasta with spicy black bean sauce
directions: Temporarily empty the cooked spaghetti in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine in the same saucepan in which you cooked the spaghetti.
Cool slightly; stir in the egg.
Pour spaghetti back in saucepan and mix well.
