Arrange cooked spaghetti over bottom of the 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Crumble browned hamburger over spaghetti; top with sauce and then sprinkle cheese over all.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease twelve 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch muffin cups.
In a large bowl, with fork, mix all the dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, with fork, beat egg slightly, stir in milk and oil. Stir egg mixture into flour mixture, just until flour mixture is moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy, not smooth).
Spoon batter into muffin cups.
Bake 20-25 minutes until golden and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Immediately remove muffins from pan. Makes 12 muffins.

title: sausage and wild rice
directions: Brown sausage, breaking with a fork to crumble.
Stir in onions and mushrooms.
Saute until soft.
Add precooked wild rice with chicken broth.
Simmer to reduce broth.
Blend in cream and heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle almonds on top and serve at once.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate zucchini set aside. Beat sugar into eggs. Add oil and vanilla. Blend well. Add zucchini and beat in remaining ingredients. Pour into 2 well greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 55 min. Test with toothpick. Cool 10 min. before removing from pans.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash, dry chicken and cut into desired size serving pieces. Coat thoroughly with seasoned flour.
Brown on all sides in fat in frypan.
Place chicken in covered baking pan.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until tender in moderate 350° oven.
Uncover the last 10 minutes.

title: macadamia coconut tart
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Roll out the pastry and use to line a 9-inch tart pan or individual tart pans. Bake the crust partially, until the pastry looks dry but is still very pale. Cool completely before filling. Reduce the temperature to 350°.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Add enough water to cook sweet potatoes like Irish potatoes. Cook until fork comes out easy and drain.
Add oleo and sugar. Cook slow until syrupy.
Keep fire
low so it doesn't stick; if need, add more sugar to taste.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange half the slices on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: roxy's spinach dip
directions: Chop water chestnuts finely.
Thaw spinach.
(It does great in microwave, with 1/2 cup water, on High for 3 to 5 minutes.)
Drain spinach on paper towels and pat dry.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in fridge for at least 1 hour.

title: quake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put nuts and coconut in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese and melted margarine and powdered sugar.
Pour or spoon over cake mix.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and dice.
Place in bowl with celery, onion, pickle and chopped hard-boiled eggs.
Fry bacon; drain.
In bacon drippings, add vinegar, sugar and eggs.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour over potatoes while hot.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: batter-dipped hot dogs
directions: Combine cornbread mix and pepper.
Add milk, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Insert wooden skewer in one end of each frankfurter.
Coat with additional flour; dip into corn meal batter.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: *To toast almonds, spread almonds evenly on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes until golden brown or spread in thin layer on microwave-safe pie pan.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until golden brown, stirring after 1 minute.

title: chinese little chicken
directions: Cut breasts in bite-size pieces.
Marinate in mixture of onions, egg, soy sauce, salt and pepper for at least 1 hour (longer will not hurt).
Flour and deep fry.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine soup, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper and carrots.
Add broccoli and mix with electric mixer.
Place melted butter or margarine in casserole dish. Pour in mixture.
Sprinkle herb stuffing mix over top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: black bean chili
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to cover with 2 tablespoons salt.
Cook according to package directions or in pressure cooker (35 minutes).
Combine rest of ingredients in pressure cooker and cook 7 minutes or cook on simmer until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaves.
Combine cooked beans and cooked vegetables and heat thoroughly.
(Beans and vegetables may be cooked together in regular pot.)

title: vegetable beef stew
directions: Cut
meat
into
3/4-inch
cubes.
In
casserole
stir together beef,
onions,
celery,
garlic,
bay leaf, bouillon, thyme, sugar,
pepper
and
1 1/2 cups water.
Microcook, covered, on High for 5 minutes.
Microcook, covered, on 50% power for 20 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and green pepepr.
Microcook on medium for 20 minutes until meat and vegetables are tender. Stir together
cornstarch and water.
Stir into meat mixture. Cook, uncovered, on High for 3 minutes.
Cook 2 minutes longer on medium.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring potatoes, water, onions and celery to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 15 minutes. Add milk and cook on high to almost boil. Mix flour, egg, salt and pepper.
Stir in flour mixture and add butter.
Reduce to low heat and cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine meat, green pepper, celery and onion in skillet; cook until meat is browned.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 35 minutes.
Serve hot on buns.

title: caramel oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, oatmeal, brown sugar and nuts in bowl.
Add egg and oil; mix.
Press half of dough into greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Pour on ice cream topping. Crumble remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: green beans deluxe
directions: Place beans in 1 inch of salted water.
Heat to boiling. Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Cover and cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes, for whole or cut beans; 5 to 10 minutes for French-style. Drain.

title: green beans with mushroom soup
directions: Drain beans and place in baking dish.
Combine milk, soup and mushrooms and add to beans.
Sprinkle with crackers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Mix 2 cups drained juice with pudding; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cool. Mix with other ingredients, except add bananas shortly before serving. Chill before adding bananas. May be done ahead. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats, cocoa and chocolate chips.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: apple cake pie
directions: Slice apples thin.
Place in well buttered 10-inch pie plate. Cover with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream butter and rest of sugar (1/2 cup) and beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator coleslaw
directions: Bring to boil the vinegar, 1/2 cup water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Let get cold.
Make a brine of 2 cups water and salt.
Soak cabbage and pepper in brine for half hour.
Drain off brine, pressing to remove most of brine.
Add to vinegar mixture with celery.
Add salt to taste.
Stir well and store in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Will keep well for 3 to 6 months.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Cook butterscotch pudding as directed on package.
When it comes to a boil, take off heat and add chocolate bits.
Stir until dissolved and smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach; remove excess water with paper towel.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Beat if refrigerated overnight.
All your friends will ask for this recipe.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add Wesson oil, buttermilk and eggs.
Mix well, then add prunes and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in two 8-inch round pans or 1 long pan, 9 x 13-inches.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: snowball salad
directions: Pour lemon juice over bananas.
Mix and pour in dish until ready to serve.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured
Bundt
pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness.
While still hot and in pan, poke the cake with fork, the more holes the better, and slowly drizzle glaze over it.

title: creamed green beans
directions: In a small saucepan melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir in cornflakes and set aside.
Melt remaining butter in a large saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, onion and sugar.
Heat and stir until bubbly.
Reduce heat and add sour cream.
Stir until smooth.
Cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes (do not boil). Fold in the beans; spread into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Sprinkle with cornflakes mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine soup, milk, onion, pimento, green pepper and black pepper.
Place over low heat, adding cheese, and stirring occasionally until the cheese is melted.
Mix macaroni and tuna in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Blend in cheese sauce.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Can add vegetable for a complete meal.

title: ribeye steak with garlic-mushroom sauce
directions: Pat steaks dry on paper towels; season both sides with salt and pepper.
In a heavy skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon butter or margarine and oil.
When oil mixture is very hot, add 2 steaks; cook to desired degree of doneness.
Using tongs, turn steaks every minute during cooking.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Place oil in a saucepan and bring to a frying temperature. Add onions and cook until soft, but not browned.
Add broccoli and stir until hot, but not cooked.
Mix soup and milk together.
Add to mixture.
Add rice.
Cook and stir until hot and mixed.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish, greased with margarine.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased cracker crumb lined 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with more cracker crumbs or cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy mocha fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with milk, sweetened condensed milk, instant coffee dissolved in water and vanilla.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in aluminum foil-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 3 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend sugar and potatoes together with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in a pie plate and sprinkle with lemon juice. In separate bowl, mix together self-rising flour and sugar, then add whipped egg to dry ingredients.
Mix to make it fluffy and crumbly.
Pour over peaches, then pour melted butter over pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cinnamon liberally.
Serve hot with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: monkey bread 2
directions: Slice biscuits into quarters. Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuits in sugar mixture.
Mix margarine and brown sugar.
Put biscuits into Bundt pan. Pour margarine mixture over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Immediately invert onto plate.

title: mincemeat shortcake
directions: Rub butter into flour until it is like bread crumbs.
Stir in sugar and spice.
Press half of mixture into a 7-inch cake tin. Spread mincemeat sparingly over and cover remaining mixture of flour.
Press down gently but firmly.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° until light brown.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cut while still warm. Use hot or cold.
Freezes well.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl add all ingredients.
Mix until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef and chili powder until beef is browned.
Spoon off fat. Stir in soup, pepper, corn, salsa and water.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Prepare corn muffin according to package.
Spoon evenly over soup mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: freezer zucchini
directions: In a large bowl mix zucchini, mango and onion.
In another bowl, mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery salt.
Pour over zucchini mixture and store in refrigerator 4 to 5 days.
Stir once a day.
Then put in containers and freeze.

title: creamy chocolate layered pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip. Spread over bottom of crust.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onion and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate to form rings.
Place in bowl and cover with milk.
Let stand at least 15 minutes.
Drain, keeping 3/4 cup of the milk.
Place pancake mix, paprika and milk (3/4 cup) into bowl.
Beat with rotary beater for 2 minutes.
Dip onion rings into batter; drain.
Fry in hot deep fat (375°) for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
If batter becomes too thick, add a little more milk.

title: chunky cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan combine first 7 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer until vegetables are tender. Add ham.
In another pan melt margarine and stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk and cook.
Stir until thickened.
Stir in cheese until melted then add to soup.
This is a delicious soup.
Serve with cornbread and salad.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as box directs.
Drain well.
Combine mayonnaise, milk, pickle relish and lemon juice.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: farina cake
directions: Bring to a boil the milk, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add farina and stir well.
Remove from heat.
Add Ricotta and eggs and stir well.
Grease a small roasting pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Place ground beef and vegetables in large skillet; brown and drain.
Add spices and place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Meanwhile, prepare and cook potatoes.
Mash and whip potatoes. Add milk and butter and spoon on top of casserole in a decorative manner.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400° until top browns slightly.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, then add onion, peppers and cheese.
Add undiluted soup.
Sift together meal, salt and combine with beaten eggs, buttermilk, oil and corn.
Pour half of bread mixture in deep greased baking dish.
Add meat mixture and top with remaining bread mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place crescent roll dough in bottom of an ungreased pizza pan.
Press to seal edges together.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat.
Immediately stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Chill until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in the cranberries, apples, oranges and pecans.
Spoon into oiled individual salad molds, a 6 1/2-cup ring mold or an 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
If desired, serve on lettuce leaves and top with a dollop of mayonnaise. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: broiled-on cake topping
directions: Mix all ingredients over one 8 or 9-inch round or square cake layer.
Place under preheated broiler for about 1 minute, watching carefully, until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and flatten flour, butter and nuts into bottom of a baking pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Allow to cool.

title: "squeekers" (fried bread)
directions: Form hunks of bread dough into 3-inch rounds and fry in butter until golden brown.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar and serve warm.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Drain peas thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish. Stir in nuts. Chop the pimento and add. Cover this with the soup mixture. Top with a layer of fine bread crumbs and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in an oven at 325° to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve while hot.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes about 1/8-inch thick.
Roll in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan and fry tomatoes until golden on both sides.
Turn down heat and cook low until soft on inside.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Get a large enough pot to fry your whole turkey in at one time.
Get the oil good and hot.
Inject your bird with the Italian seasoning.
You can use a baster for this.
Fry the turkey at 4 minutes per pound.
Best thing you ever ate.

title: holiday cider drink
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cook for 2 hours at 200° until warm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream all ingredients except shrimp and celery.
Add shrimp and celery.
Mix and chill thoroughly.

title: my mother's 10x sugar cake
directions: Blend margarine and sugar.
Add flour with eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by level tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown. Makes 4 dozen small cookies.

title: easy camping bread
directions: Pour melted margarine into 8-inch cake pan.
Add celery seed, dill weed and onion salt.
Spread on bottom of cake pan.
Cut biscuits into quarters and place in pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Put in casserole and top with crushed crackers and 4 tablespoons butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash
directions: Brown hamburger.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after 1/2 hour.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in a
300° oven for 1 1/2 hours. This will make 2 large loaf pans.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Take a slice of ham, spread with cream cheese.
Put 1 pickle spear and 1/2 slice green onion on ham with cream cheese and roll closed.
Slice into bite size pieces.
Great.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Top with Italian dressing and marinate.
Great summertime salad.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread according to package directions.
Crumble. Add onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and cheese.
Stir well.
Add Miracle Whip.
Stir well.

title: cheese pecan nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Open biscuits and divide each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece and spread a layer of cheese.
Top each piece and spread layer of cheese and top with pecan half. Pull dough up around cheese and pecan, pressing together to form a ball.
Place on baking sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°. Cool on rack.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Boil
chicken
breasts; debone and set aside.
Stir in 1 can cream
of celery soup in chicken broth.
Cook noodles slow until tender
and
drain.
Add
noodles and chicken to chicken broth. Add cheese, a little at a time, until cheese is melted. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool!

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together. Chill for 1 hour. Roll into 1 inch balls, roll in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: grandma edna's bread pudding(light recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, bring apples, raisins and apple juice concentrate to a boil over medium heat. Cook until apples are soft (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Let cool to room temperature.
In another saucepan, boil milk and add vanilla and spices.
Combine milk with cooked apples and fold in egg whites.
Add bread pieces to mixture and fold until mixed evenly.

title: chicken cacciatora
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano. Remove from pan and sear garlic, then mushrooms.
After this is done, put chicken back in pan (Dutch oven preferably).
Pour tomatoes over.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Uncover and cook, until chicken is done.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water so you will have about 4 1/2 to 5 cups broth. Take chicken out when cooked.
Cook rice in broth.
Cook broccoli until tender in a large casserole.
Combine soups, cheese (diced), broccoli, rice and chicken (diced) in casserole
dish. Bake 30 minutes in oven at 350° or 15 minutes in microwave or until cheese is melted.
Stir and serve.

title: parmesan toast
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast the bread on both sides until crisp, but not golden, about 7 to 8 minutes.
Rub the rounds with garlic; brush with oil and sprinkle with a thin layer of cheese and toast another 7 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix 2 cups graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine at room temperature.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Do not bake.)

title: chocolate fluff pudding
directions: Put milk in a bowl.
Dip Oreo cookies in milk.
Place a layer on
bottom
of pan or dish.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip on top. Repeat to make 2 layers.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: zippy barbecue sauce
directions: In small saucepan, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring often until slightly thickened.
Turn into hot, sterilized wide-mouth bottles or jars; cover tightly.
Use as basting sauce for pork or beef.
Keeps refrigerated up to 4 weeks.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake 30 minutes.
Pour fat from baking dish.
Discard. Season with salt and pepper.
Drain juice from pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine 1/2 cup pineapple juice, honey, ketchup, soy sauce, oil, cashews, celery and garlic.
Pour juice mixture over chicken. Cover tightly with foil. Bake 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Top chicken with pineapple slices. Bake 5 minutes or until pineapple is warmed through. Serve hot over rice.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy; beat in egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and pumpkin.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: microwave pizza wheels
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, salt and 1/4 teaspoon oregano. Shape into 4 patties, rising the edge 1/4 inch to form a center well.
In baking dish, arrange patties.
Heat 5 1/2 minutes; drain.
Fill center well with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with oregano; heat 1 to 2 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Let stand, covered, 4 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and turn into shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with party rye as a hot spread.

title: breaded turkey cutlets
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip meat into dressing.
Press into coating.
Microwave on 70% for 7 to 11 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss together spinach, endive, jicama and onion rings.
Blend dressing and soy sauce.
Pour over salad and toss.
Serve at once. Serves 4.

title: sunshine ice cream pie
directions: Spread ice cream over crust; spread sherbet over ice cream. Freeze for at least 3 hours. Top with whipped topping. Cover and freeze. Thirty minutes before serving, remove pie from freezer; arrange oranges on top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and mash with a fork.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet until brown on bottom, about 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add 3 tablespoons chopped ham and simmer 1/2 hour more.

title: pasta, protein, veggie dish
directions: Cook spaghetti and steam the vegetables.

title: coke roast
directions: Remove excess fat from roast, score roast all over with 3/4 inch squares, 1/2 inch deep. Rub in seasonings. Sear roast on all sides in oil. Place in crock pot, cover with chili sauce and Coke. Cook 6 hours on high or 9 hours on low setting. If you prefer, roast can be cooked in 350° oven, covered, for 3-1/2 hours.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked eggs in halves.
Slip out yolks.
Mash with a fork and mix in rest of ingredients.
Refill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it up lightly.

title: nutty crisps
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and place on greased baking sheet in rough mounds.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until barely tinged brown.
Cool for 15 minutes and dredge in confectioners sugar.

title: stack a roll stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix beef, mushrooms and two-thirds of onion in 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat soup.
Stir in 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour over meat.
Cut biscuits in half. Arrange cut side down around edge.
Add remaining onion in center. Mix remaining sour cream, egg, celery seed and salt.
Pour this over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown pork chops in hot oil.
Place apple slices in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Dot with butter.
Top with pork chops.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Makes six servings.

title: meridith's favorite meat sauce
directions: Saute garlic in small amount of olive oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Add puree, paste and 1 1/2 puree cans of water.
Brown turkey; use Pam or turkey will stick to pan.
Drain and add turkey to sauce. Brown sausage; drain and add to sauce.
Add bay leaves, basil and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in bowl.
Beat eggs in separate bowl; add milk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until just mixed.
Batter should be lumpy. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: turkey tomato stew
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients, boil, uncovered, 30 minutes. Stir in turkey and peas.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: sausage casserole(great for a brunch)
directions: Tear bread into bite-size pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crumble sausage; cook and drain.
Spread sausage or ham over bread.
Add mushrooms and top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: In a food processor or blender, combine seasonings, 1/4 cup oil, vinegar, egg and lemon juice.
Process for 2 minutes or so. Slowly add remaining oil, teaspoon by teaspoon, blending until oil is used.
Blend in boiling water.
Add NutraSweet. makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 inches deep oil to 375°.
Combine corn meal mix, milk, egg and onion; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot oil, frying only a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Cook first three ingredients until rhubarb is done.
Set off stove and add the jello.
Put into jars and seal.

title: oatmeal toffee lizzies
directions: Combine sugar and shortening with a spoon.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt gradually, mixing well.
Stir in oats, chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 15 to 30 minutes or until dough handles easily.
(If you are in a hurry, spray your hands with cooking spray and shape.)
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet. Flatten with a glass bottom.
Bake at 350° until brown around the edges.
Bake 12 minutes for crisp cookies, 10 minutes for soft. Remove; cool and store airtight.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: carrot ring
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 60 minutes.

title: daddy's coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately to other mixture.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan in 350°
oven for 1 hour.
Cook until top is good and brown.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix well.
Add enough half and half to make it spread or for dipping chips in.

title: christmas holly cookies
directions: Melt
stick butter and 16 large marshmallows in large saucepan.
When
melted,
and
thoroughly
blended, add vanilla flavoring and blend in green food coloring.
Gradually add corn flakes
and
stir
until
thoroughly
covered. While still hot, place 3
cinnamon candies on top of each cookie which have been dropped by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: walnut cinnamon coffeecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil 8-inch square pan.
Combine walnuts, brown sugar and cinnamon in small bowl; set aside. Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda in another bowl and mix to blend.
Combine oil, buttermilk, egg and vanilla in third bowl.
Then add to dry ingredients.
Stir just to combine. Do not overmix.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, salt and parsley flakes. Mix well. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add milk to can of soup; blend well. Pour over vegetables; add cheese. Bring to boil until cheese melts. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Combine water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion and salt and cook for 10 to 12 minutes.
Prepare white sauce by blending butter, flour and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add vegetables (undrained).
Stir in ham and grated cheese.
Heat and serve.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Slice and arrange cookies on pizza pan.
Bake according to package; let cool.
Mix cream cheese and spread on top of cookie mix.
Clean and drain strawberries.
Mix berries with glaze and spread on top of cream cheese.
Refrigerate until good and cold. Very delicious.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Put flour and all seasonings in a large bowl and mix well. Add frog legs, cover bowl and shake to coat all frog legs thoroughly with dry mixture.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with additional salt and enjoy.

title: hamburger hash
directions: After browning and draining hamburger, add all other ingredients into a large, deep oven-safe pan.
Cover with foil. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: moist chicken dressing
directions: Use broth from hen/turkey or a can of broth.
Use corn bread already cooked; grind celery and onions together, then soak bread (3/4) and corn bread (all) in broth (1 can).

title: good-n-ugly cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over butter and nuts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Shred zucchini.
Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour into two greased loaf pans or one tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and turn out on cake rack to completely cool.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Brown in butter.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: pineapple coconut squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with fork or pastry blender, then knead with hands until soft dough.
Press dough into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and up the sides about 1/2-inch.
Prick with fork. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread pineapple over crust.
Mix sugar, egg, melted butter and coconut. Spread over the pineapple and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: ed's chili chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients with an * beside them to make sauce. Simmer chicken breasts until tender, then bone and shred to bite-size pieces.
Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch strips.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with layer of strips, then layer of chicken, strips, sauce, etc.
Shred cheese and layer over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Best when reheated the next day.
Reheat, covered.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all the ingredients in a large glass Pyrex dish.
Mix the same amount of mayonnaise and salad dressing, enough to cover the salad.
Spread over the top.
This is as pretty as it is good. You may also add a layer of chopped tomatoes; best in the summer when they are fresh.

title: peanut pillows
directions: Melt chocolate
pieces
and
shortening
over low heat; stir in
peanut
butter
and
powdered
sugar.
Dip
cereal in chocolate mixture, coating all sides; gently shake off excess. Roll in chopped peanuts.
Cool on rack.
Store in refrigerator or in a very cold place.

title: crab spread
directions: If necessary, remove cartilage from crabmeat.
In a medium bowl, combine Miracle Whip, parsley, chives, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add chopped cooked egg whites, crabmeat and diced cucumber.
Toss.
Refrigerate, covered, until well chilled, about 1 hour.
Serve as a spread with fat-free saltine crackers as an appetizer.
This can also be served over lettuce leaves as a salad.
Yields 8 servings as an appetizer or 4 salads.

title: lemon cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Put cake flour, sugar, baking powder,
salt
and	grated	lemon
rind into mixer bowl.
Turn mixer
on
low and mix 10 seconds to aerate.
Add butter; beat 30 seconds or until well incorporated.
Add eggs, lemon juice and extract.
Beat
until
mixture is light in color, about 2 minutes. Spoon
into
a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan (8-inch
is better).
Bake
for 30 to 40 minutes or until the cake
springs back lightly when pressed and a toothpick comes out clean.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a pie plate, layer the following items in the order listed: cream cheese, onions, beans, salsa, grated cheese, olives.
*You may use cream cheese with onions.
In this case, omit the green onions from the recipe.

title: rice salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip per directions on package.
Cook rice per direction on package.
After rice has cooled, mix all ingredients together.

title: pineapple rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake
according to directions on box.
While still hot, punch holes
in cake.
Pour milk and caramel topping over cake. Chill.
Spread
Cool
Whip	over chilled cake.
Crumble candy bars and sprinkle on top.

title: venison loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except bacon.
Mix well.
Shape the meat mixture into a loaf.
Top loaf with 3 slices of bacon.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with potato and vegetable.

title: yogurt cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise in halves (or thin slices), then slice about 1/4-inch thick or cube.
Pulverize garlic cloves with mint and salt.
Add to yogurt.
Mix well.
Add cucumbers, mixing well.
Serve cold.

title: sweet and sour baby carrot salad
directions: Canned sliced carrots can be used; drain and rinse.

title: good dressing for vegetable salad
directions: Mix well and pour over vegetables.
You may use broccoli tops, white raisins, onion rings, celery, bacon (crumbled), nuts, cauliflower or whatever.
After mixing, refrigerate overnight. Delicious!

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and crumble sausage. Cook noodles according to package directions and drain. Mix sausage, cheese and pimento, leaving enough cheese to sprinkle on top. Mix soup with 1/4 can water. Mix all well and add noodles. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Cut up catfish in 2-inch strips; soak in stale beer for a couple of hours.
Drain; rinse and make an egg wash, then roll in instant potatoes.
Deep fry until done.

title: french toast
directions: Butter bread with softened butter and set aside.
Mix eggs, salt and pepper with wire whisk.
Place 6 slices of bread into margarine-greased 3-quart flat Pyrex baking dish.
Pour 1/2 egg mixture over evenly.
Place second layer of buttered bread in dish and pour remaining egg mixture over it.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture, then pecans.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until bubbly.
Serve immediately with fruit salad.

title: crosscut pickle slices
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly and drain.
Slice, unpeeled, into 1/8-inch slices.
Add onions and garlic.
Add salt and mix thoroughly.
Cover with crushed ice or cubes.
Let stand 3 hours.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate syrup.
Beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour half of batter into greased tube pan.
Add syrup to remaining batter and blend well. Pour over batter in pan.
Don't stir to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ginger drink
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan and cook over a low flame for 40 minutes.
Pour liquid into warm cups; serve hot.

title: plantation peach short cake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease two 8-inch round cake pans.
Spoon flour into a measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl combine flour and brown sugar; cut in margarine until it is like coarse meal.
Add pecans, half and half and egg; stir just until a soft dough forms.
Spread dough evenly into pans.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from pans.
Cool. Serve with sliced peaches and whipped cream between layers and on top.

title: chocolate mincemeat bars
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking soda and semi-sweet chips.
Mix with a wooden spoon.
Add mincemeat.
Spread on greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Test with toothpick.
Bars are moist; delicious warm or cool.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Puree strawberries in blender until almost smooth.
Mix with remaining liquids.
Freeze overnight.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt in a mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Sift flour and soda; add to first mixture and beat well.
Add apples and pecans; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sausage manicotti
directions: 1. Mix together 1/2 of parmesan cheese, ricotta, 1/2 grat ed mozzarella, parsley, garlic, eggs, oregano, Salt & Pepper.
Put some sauce in bottom of pan. 2. Assemble manicotti.
Cut lasagna noodles in half short ways.

Place a Tbsp. or so of ricotta mixture & some sausage and wrap with noodles, seam side down in pan. Finish all ingredients then cover generously with sauce and rest of cheese. 3. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Blend in egg white, oil and milk.
Stir until flour is moistened.

title: indonesian-style beef and bananas
directions: Combine soy sauce, lemon juice, molasses, garlic, ginger and red pepper.
Place beef in a plastic bag set in a bowl.
Pour soy mixture over meat; seal bag.
Marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain, reserving marinade.
